5248         # end. If we wish to simply reproduce ShapeEnv instances even after this call,
5249         # this method should also be recorded.
5250         if self.check_recorded_events:
5251             shape_env = replay_shape_env_events(self.events)
5252             self.check_equal(shape_env)
5253 
5254         assert len(placeholders) == len(sources), (
5255             f"len({placeholders}) != len({sources})"
5256         )
5257         Tensorlike = (torch.Tensor, FakeTensorMeta)
5258 
5259         def _create_no_constraints_context(t: Tensor) -> StatelessSymbolicContext:
5260             return StatelessSymbolicContext(
5261                 # Ignored; only the constraints part is relevant below.
5262                 dynamic_sizes=[DimDynamic.DYNAMIC] * t.dim(),
5263                 dynamic_strides=[DimDynamic.INFER_STRIDE] * t.dim(),
5264                 constraint_sizes=[None] * t.dim(),
5265                 constraint_strides=[None] * t.dim(),
5266             )
5267 
5268         # Expand optional inputs, or verify invariants are upheld
5269         if input_contexts is None:
5270             input_contexts = [
5271                 _create_no_constraints_context(t) if isinstance(t, Tensorlike) else None
5272                 for t in placeholders
5273             ]
5274         else:
5275             assert len(input_contexts) == len(placeholders)
5276             for i, (t, context) in enumerate(zip(placeholders, input_contexts)):
5277                 if isinstance(t, Tensorlike):
5278                     if context is None:
5279                         input_contexts[i] = _create_no_constraints_context(t)
5280                 else:
5281                     assert isinstance(t, (SymInt, int, SymFloat, float))
5282                     assert not isinstance(context, list)
5283 
5284         # It took a lot of sweat to figure out the algorithm here.  Let's
5285         # explain how it works.
5286         #
5287         # The ShapeEnv lifecycle looks something like this:
5288         #
5289         # - For each input, you either generate a fresh Sympy symbol (s0) to
5290         #   represent its value (a binding site), or you reuse some
5291         #   preexisting symbol or expression, skipping the symbol allocation
5292         #   (e.g., duck sizing to a preexisting symbol, or expressing a
5293         #   stride as a multiplication of a separate stride and size.)
5294         #   Naively, you might expect to bind a fresh Sympy symbol for
5295         #   every input, but this is fairly wasteful as most of these
5296         #   symbols immediately simplify away, and if you don't eagerly
5297         #   specialize, e.g., 0/1 symbols, you end up with very complicated
5298         #   expressions that are not optimizable in practice.
5299         #
5300         # - You perform some compute on these symbols, occasionally
5301         #   introducing guards on boolean expressions on these symbols.
5302         #   In particular, whenever we guard on equality (_maybe_guard_rel),
5303         #   we can simplify shapes; e.g., when s0 == s1 * 2, we can now
5304         #   replace all occurrences of s0 with s1 * 2.  Sometimes, a
5305         #   boolean expression evaluation doesn't introduce a guard, as
5306         #   the guard is already entailed by the simplifications we have
5307         #   applied.
5308         #
5309         # - In the end, you have a bunch of replacements (saying how to
5310         #   simplify shapes) and a bunch of guards (all the equality guards
5311         #   are trivial, because they're covered by the replacements).
5312         #
5313         # From the ShapeEnv, we must generate a Python expression that, when
5314         # evaluated on a set of inputs, tells us whether or not these boolean
5315         # expressions would have evaluated in the same way.  However,
5316         # we cannot easily compute this, as we elide recording boolean
5317         # expressions when we think they are vacuously true.  Thus, we seek
5318         # an approximation: we must generate an expression, if true, would have
5319         # produced an "equivalent" ShapeEnv, which would answer guard
5320         # expressions in the same way.
5321         #
5322         # Our notion of equivalence is a bit subtle.  For example, consider
5323         # the ShapeEnv created from an input of size (5, 4) versus (4, 4)
5324         # (no other guards.)  Duck sizing would generate (s0, s1) in the first
5325         # case but (s0, s0) in the second.  We do NOT assume that size
5326         # variables are disjoint; so in fact a graph that assumes the input
5327         # could be (s0, s1) subsumes (s0, s0) (setting s0 == s1), but not
5328         # vice versa.  However, consider an analogous case (1,) versus (2,).
5329         # Duck sizing generates (1,) and (s0,); the (s0,) graph does NOT
5330         # subsume the (1,) graph because we assume that any size variables
5331         # is NOT 0/1 (and make simplifications according to this; e.g., if
5332         # we queried s0 == 0, we would immediately return False without
5333         # returning a guard.)
5334         #
5335         # So, it is perhaps easier to flip things on their head: the guard
5336         # expressions we generate here say what simplifications are valid,
5337         # and what are not. Below, we explain each of the guard expressions
5338         # we generate
5339 
5340         # TODO: Make this more efficient by binding all the size/stride/offsets
5341         # to locals before performing tests on them.
5342 
5343         from torch._dynamo.source import TensorProperty, TensorPropertySource
5344 
5345         # Actual codegen must be delayed as we don't necessarily know what
5346         # the symbol mapping is
5347         input_guards = []
5348 
5349         symbol_to_source: dict[sympy.Symbol, list[Source]] = collections.defaultdict(
5350             list
5351         )
5352         symbol_to_constraints: defaultdict[sympy.Symbol, set[Constraint]] = (
5353             collections.defaultdict(set)
5354         )
5355         constraint_violations: list[tuple[bool, str, Callable[[], str]]] = []
5356 
5357         printers: list[_ShapeGuardPrinter] = []
5358         py_printer = ShapeGuardPythonPrinter(
5359             symbol_to_source, source_ref, self.var_to_sources
5360         )
5361         for lang in langs:
5362             if lang in ["python", "verbose_python"]:
5363                 printers.append(py_printer)
5364             elif lang == "cpp":
5365                 printers.append(
5366                     _ShapeGuardCppPrinter(
5367                         symbol_to_source, source_ref, self.var_to_sources
5368                     )
5369                 )
5370             else:
5371                 raise NotImplementedError(f"Unknown lang: {lang}")
5372 
5373         def record_constraint_violation(
5374             warn_only: bool,
5375             debug_name: str,
5376             msg: str,
5377             hint: Optional[Callable[[], str]] = None,
5378         ) -> None:
5379             constraint_violations.append(
5380                 (warn_only, debug_name, lambda: f"{msg}{hint()}" if hint else msg)
5381             )
5382 
5383         def is_dim(src: object) -> TypeGuard[TensorPropertySource]:
5384             return (
5385                 isinstance(src, TensorPropertySource)
5386                 and src.prop is TensorProperty.SIZE
5387             )
5388 
5389         if equalities_inputs:
5390             source_index = {}
5391             for i, src in enumerate(sources):
5392                 source_index[src.name()] = i
5393 
5394             def get_expression(tensor_dim_src: Source) -> sympy.Expr:
5395                 fake = placeholders[source_index[tensor_dim_src.base.name()]]  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5396                 assert tensor_dim_src.idx is not None  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5397                 symint = fake.shape[tensor_dim_src.idx]  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5398                 if isinstance(symint, torch.SymInt):
5399                     return symint.node.expr
5400                 else:
5401                     assert type(symint) is int, f"Expected int, got {type(symint)}"
5402                     return sympy.Integer(symint)
5403 
5404             for src1, src2 in equalities_inputs.source_pairs:
5405                 expr1, expr2 = get_expression(src1), get_expression(src2)  # type: ignore[]
5406                 # Check whether given input shape values satisfy a specified equation s = s'.
5407                 # - Raise when the equation was violated by the given input shape values.
5408                 # - Otherwise issue a guard to constrain them.
5409                 concrete_val = self.evaluate_expr(sympy.Eq(expr1, expr2))
5410                 if not concrete_val:
5411                     raise ConstraintViolationError(
5412                         f"{src1.name()} = {expr1 if isinstance(expr1, int) else expr1.xreplace(self.var_to_val)}"
5413                         " is not equal to "
5414                         f"{src2.name()} = {expr2 if isinstance(expr2, int) else expr2.xreplace(self.var_to_val)}"
5415                     )
5416 
5417             for srcEq, root, fn in equalities_inputs.derived_equalities:
5418                 expr1 = get_expression(srcEq)
5419                 # recall that root is either a phantom symbol or an input source
5420                 expr2, debug_name = (
5421                     (root, self.var_to_sources[root][0].name())
5422                     if isinstance(root, sympy.Symbol)
5423                     else (get_expression(root), self._debug_name(root))
5424                 )
5425                 expr2_ = fn(expr2)
5426                 # Check whether given input shape values satisfy a specified equation s = fn(s').
5427                 # - Raise when the equation was violated by the given input shape values.
5428                 # - Otherwise issue a guard to constrain them.
5429                 concrete_val = self.evaluate_expr(sympy.Eq(expr1, expr2_))
5430                 if not concrete_val:
5431                     raise ConstraintViolationError(
5432                         f"Expected input {srcEq.name()} to be equal to "
5433                         f"{fn(sympy.Symbol(debug_name))}, "
5434                         f"where {debug_name} = {expr2.xreplace(self.var_to_val)}, "
5435                         f"but got {expr1.xreplace(self.var_to_val)}"
5436                     )
5437 
5438             for phantom_symbol in equalities_inputs.phantom_symbols:
5439                 # we created additional phantom symbols that are not input shape dimensions
5440                 symbol_to_source[phantom_symbol].extend(
5441                     self.var_to_sources[phantom_symbol]
5442                 )
5443 
5444         # How do we know what the value of s0 is?  Fresh variables can only be
5445         # bound by inputs, so there MUST be some other input which binds the
5446         # variable.  If there is no such input, this is an error in our
5447         # system.  We record where all symbols come from, to help you diagnose
5448         # why those symbols didn't occur.
5449         #
5450         # In fact, generally speaking it is only possible for the "outermost"
5451         # user of a ShapeEnv to evaluate the guards, because some inputs may
5452         # not be available to inner levels.  For example, Dynamo can guard on
5453         # tensors that never actually become graph arguments (they are
5454         # pruned).  In this case, only Dynamo knows about these arguments.
5455         def track_symint(
5456             source: Source, val: IntLikeType, constraint: DimConstraint = None
5457         ) -> None:
5458             log.debug("track_symint %s %s %s", LazyString(source.name), val, constraint)
5459             assert not isinstance(val, SymInt) or is_symbolic(val)
5460 
5461             if isinstance(val, SymInt) and val.node.maybe_as_int() is not None:
5462                 val = val.node.maybe_as_int()
5463 
5464             if isinstance(val, SymInt):
5465                 s = val.node.expr
5466                 if isinstance(s, sympy.Symbol):
5467                     symbol_to_source[s].append(source)
5468                     if constraint is not None and not isinstance(
5469                         constraint, RelaxedUnspecConstraint
5470                     ):
5471                         symbol_to_constraints[s].add(constraint)
5472                 else:
5473                     constraint_violated = False
5474                     if isinstance(constraint, StrictMinMaxConstraint):
5475                         # try inferring the ranges of the expr s
5476                         sym_vrs = {
5477                             x: self.var_to_range.get(x, None) for x in s.free_symbols
5478                         }
5479                         if any(vr is None for vr in sym_vrs.values()):
5480                             # some of the free symbols in s don't have ranges
5481                             constraint_violated = True
5482                     elif isinstance(constraint, RelaxedUnspecConstraint):
5483                         if s.is_number:
5484                             i = int(s)
5485                             # Don't complain about 0/1 specialization, we
5486                             # expect to have to compile in this case anyway
5487                             if i not in (0, 1):
5488                                 constraint_violated = True
5489                     if constraint_violated:
5490                         assert constraint is not None
5491 
5492                         def hint(s: sympy.Expr) -> str:
5493                             sexpr = py_printer.doprint(s)
5494                             return f"{sexpr}."
5495 
5496                         var_with_range = self._render_range_for_constraint_violation(
5497                             source, constraint
5498                         )
5499                         msg = (
5500                             f"Not all values of {var_with_range} are valid because "
5501                             f"{self._debug_name(source)} was inferred to be equal to "
5502                         )
5503                         record_constraint_violation(
5504                             constraint.warn_only,
5505                             self._debug_name(source),
5506                             msg,
5507                             hint=functools.partial(hint, s),
5508                         )
5509 
5510                 input_guards.append((source, s))
5511             else:
5512                 s = sympy.Integer(val)
5513                 input_guards.append((source, s))
5514                 constraint_violated = False
5515                 if isinstance(constraint, StrictMinMaxConstraint):
5516                     if not (
5517                         s == constraint.vr.lower == constraint.vr.upper
5518                     ):  # allow static constraints
5519                         constraint_violated = True
5520                 elif isinstance(constraint, RelaxedUnspecConstraint):
5521                     # Don't complain about 0/1 specialization, we
5522                     # expect to have to compile in this case anyway
5523                     if val not in (0, 1):
5524                         constraint_violated = True
5525                 if constraint_violated:
5526                     assert constraint is not None
5527                     var_with_range = self._render_range_for_constraint_violation(
5528                         source, constraint
5529                     )
5530                     user_stack = self.user_specialization_stacks.get(source, None)
5531                     framework_stack = self.framework_specialization_stacks.get(
5532                         source, None
5533                     )
5534                     msg = (
5535                         f"You marked {self._debug_name(source)} as dynamic but your code "
5536                         f"specialized it to be a constant ({val}). If you're using mark_dynamic, "
5537                         f"either remove it or use maybe_mark_dynamic. If you're using Dim.DYNAMIC, "
5538                         f"replace it with either Dim.STATIC or Dim.AUTO."
5539                         + (
5540                             "\n\nFramework stack:\n" + "".join(framework_stack.format())
5541                             if framework_stack
5542                             else ""
5543                         )
5544                         + (
5545                             "\n\nUser stack:\n" + "".join(user_stack.format())
5546                             if user_stack
5547                             else ""
5548                         )
5549                     )
5550                     record_constraint_violation(
5551                         constraint.warn_only, self._debug_name(source), msg
5552                     )
5553 
5554         def track_symfloat(source: Source, val: FloatLikeType) -> None:
5555             log.debug("track_symfloat %s %s", LazyString(source.name), val)
5556             assert not isinstance(val, SymFloat) or is_symbolic(val)
5557 
5558             if isinstance(val, SymFloat) and val.node.maybe_as_float() is not None:
5559                 val = val.node.maybe_as_float()
5560 
5561             if isinstance(val, SymFloat):
5562                 s = val.node.expr
5563                 if isinstance(s, sympy.Symbol):
5564                     symbol_to_source[s].append(source)
5565                 input_guards.append((source, s))
5566             else:
5567                 s = sympy.Float(val)
5568                 input_guards.append((source, s))
5569 
5570         for t, source, context in zip(placeholders, sources, input_contexts):
5571             if isinstance(source, str):
5572                 from torch._dynamo.source import LocalSource
5573 
5574                 source = LocalSource(source)
5575             assert isinstance(source, Source)
5576             if t is None:
5577                 continue
5578             if isinstance(t, (SymInt, int)):
5579                 constraint = (
5580                     None if context is None else getattr(context, "constraint", None)
5581                 )
5582                 track_symint(source, t, constraint)
5583                 continue
5584             elif isinstance(t, (SymFloat, float)):
5585                 track_symfloat(source, t)
5586                 continue
5587             assert isinstance(t, Tensorlike)
5588             if is_traceable_wrapper_subclass(t):
5589                 from torch._dynamo.source import AttrSource
5590 
5591                 assert isinstance(context, SubclassSymbolicContext)
5592 
5593                 # For subclasses, we need to track symints on BOTH the outer
5594                 # and inner tensors.
5595                 # TODO: type this better
5596                 sources_tensors_constraints: list[tuple[Source, Any, Any, Any]] = [
5597                     (source, t, context.constraint_sizes, context.constraint_strides)
5598                 ]
5599                 attrs, _ = t.__tensor_flatten__()
5600                 for attr in attrs:
5601                     inner_t = getattr(t, attr)
5602                     inner_context = context.inner_contexts[attr]
5603                     sources_tensors_constraints.append(
5604                         (
5605                             AttrSource(source, attr),
5606                             inner_t,
5607                             inner_context.constraint_sizes,  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5608                             inner_context.constraint_strides,  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5609                         )
5610                     )
5611             else:
5612                 sources_tensors_constraints = [
5613                     (source, t, context.constraint_sizes, context.constraint_strides)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
5614                 ]
5615 
5616             for (
5617                 src,
5618                 curr_t,
5619                 constraint_size,
5620                 constraint_stride,
5621             ) in sources_tensors_constraints:
5622                 if is_sparse_any(curr_t):
5623                     for i, ss in enumerate(curr_t.size()):
5624                         property_source = TensorPropertySource(
5625                             src, TensorProperty.SIZE, i
5626                         )
5627                         track_symint(property_source, ss, constraint_size[i])
5628                 else:
5629                     for i, ss in enumerate(curr_t.size()):
5630                         property_source = TensorPropertySource(
5631                             src, TensorProperty.SIZE, i
5632                         )
5633                         track_symint(property_source, ss, constraint_size[i])
5634                     for i, ss in enumerate(curr_t.stride()):
5635                         property_source = TensorPropertySource(
5636                             src, TensorProperty.STRIDE, i
5637                         )
5638                         track_symint(property_source, ss, constraint_stride[i])
5639                     track_symint(
5640                         TensorPropertySource(src, TensorProperty.STORAGE_OFFSET),
5641                         curr_t.storage_offset(),
5642                     )
5643 
5644         # 1. Every input must equal the final simplified symbolic expression
5645         #    stored on the placeholder.  Given a placeholder (s0*2, s1),
5646         #    if we have an input (2, 3), we must show s0*2 == 2 and s1 == 3.
5647         #    This does a lot of work: it covers duck sizing and equality guards.
5648         all_exprs: list[list[str]] = [[] for _ in langs]
5649         self.dim_constraints = DimConstraints(
5650             symbol_to_source,
5651             self.var_to_val,
5652             set(symbol_to_constraints.keys()),
5653             self.source_name_to_debug_name,
5654         )
5655 
5656         if not _simplified:
5657             for source, expr in input_guards:
5658                 srcname = source.name()
5659                 if self._translation_validation_enabled:
5660                     # Ignore sources that were not turned into SymInts.
5661                     if srcname in self.source_to_symbol:
5662                         self._add_target_expr(
5663                             sympy.Eq(self.source_to_symbol[srcname], expr)
5664                         )
5665 
5666                 # Small optimization
5667                 if (
5668                     isinstance(expr, sympy.Symbol)
5669                     and symbol_to_source.get(expr)
5670                     and source == symbol_to_source[expr][0]
5671                 ):
5672                     continue
5673 
5674                 # This logic excludes static values found on tensors from guarding, because
5675                 # dynamo's check_tensor_fn does that (see guards.cpp).
5676                 # However, for non tensor sources, we still need to guard here.
5677                 if ignore_static and isinstance(source, TensorPropertySource):
5678                     if expr.is_number:
5679                         self.log.debug(
5680                             "Skipping guard %s", f"{source_ref(source)} == {expr}"
5681                         )
5682                         continue
5683 
5684                 if is_dim(source):
5685                     self.dim_constraints.add_equality(source, expr)
5686 
5687                 for exprs, printer, lang in zip(all_exprs, printers, langs):
5688                     res = f"{printer.print_source(source)} == {printer.doprint(expr)}"
5689 
5690                     if lang == "verbose_python":
5691                         if (s0 := self.source_to_var.get(srcname)) is not None:
5692                             if source != self.var_to_sources[s0][0]:
5693                                 res = (
5694                                     f"{res}  # duck sizing added this equality because these "
5695                                     f"variables had the same size {self.var_to_val[s0]} "
5696                                     "(to avoid this specialization, set torch.fx.experimental._config.use_duck_shape = False)"
5697                                 )
5698                             elif (sloc := self.replacements_slocs.get(s0)) is not None:
5699                                 res = f"{res}  # {sloc}"
5700                             else:
5701                                 res = f"{res}  # (unknown var {s0}, please file a bug)"
5702                         else:
5703                             res = f"{res}  # (unknown source {srcname}, please file a bug)"
5704                     exprs.append(res)
5705 
5706                 if (
5707                     isinstance(source, TensorPropertySource)
5708                     and source.prop is TensorProperty.SIZE
5709                     and equalities_inputs
5710                     and len(expr.free_symbols) == 1
5711                 ):
5712                     symbol = next(iter(expr.free_symbols))
5713                     if (
5714                         isinstance(expr, sympy.Symbol)
5715                         and expr in symbol_to_constraints
5716                         and not equalities_inputs.is_equal(
5717                             source, symbol_to_source[expr][0]
5718                         )
5719                     ):
5720                         msg = (
5721                             f"The values of {self._debug_name(source)} = {source.name()} and "
5722                             f"{self._debug_name(symbol_to_source[expr][0])} = {symbol_to_source[expr][0].name()} "
5723                             "must always be equal."
5724                         )
5725                         record_constraint_violation(
5726                             equalities_inputs.warn_only, self._debug_name(source), msg
5727                         )
5728 
5729                     if (
5730                         not isinstance(expr, sympy.Symbol)
5731                         and symbol in symbol_to_constraints
5732                         and not equalities_inputs.is_derived(
5733                             source,
5734                             symbol_to_source[symbol][0],
5735                             lambda x: expr.xreplace({symbol: x}),
5736                         )
5737                     ):
5738                         src = symbol_to_source[symbol][0]
5739                         msg = (
5740                             f"The values of {self._debug_name(source)} = {source.name()} must always be related to "
5741                             f"the values of {self._debug_name(src)} = {src.name()} by "
5742                             f"{self._debug_name(source)} = {expr.xreplace({symbol: sympy.sympify(self._debug_name(src))})}."
5743                         )
5744                         record_constraint_violation(
5745                             equalities_inputs.warn_only, self._debug_name(source), msg
5746                         )
5747 
5748                 # NB: Not necessary to report constraint violations here:
5749                 # constraints are guaranteed to be on symbols (we've already
5750                 # caught constants and non-atomic expressions), so we only
5751                 # have relational constraints, but we don't support those
5752                 # at the moment
5753 
5754         # 2. Every guard must evaluate to True (but remember many guards
5755         #    like s0 == s1*2 because trivial due to simplification)
5756         issued = set()
5757 
5758         def issue_guard(guard: ShapeGuard) -> None:
5759             expr = self.simplify(guard.expr)
5760 
5761             # Avoid re-issueing the same guard.
5762             if expr in issued:
5763                 return
5764 
5765             issued.add(expr)
5766 
5767             try:
5768                 is_trivial = False
5769                 if any(
5770                     is_dim(source)
5771                     for s in expr.free_symbols
5772                     for source in symbol_to_source[s]
5773                 ):
5774                     assert self.dim_constraints is not None
5775                     is_trivial = self.dim_constraints.add(expr)
5776 
5777                 for exprs, printer, lang in zip(all_exprs, printers, langs):
5778                     guard_expr = printer.doprint(expr)
5779                     if lang == "verbose_python":
5780                         guard_expr = f"{guard_expr}  # {guard.sloc}"
5781                     exprs.append(guard_expr)
5782 
5783                 self._add_target_expr(expr)
5784                 # A non-relational constraint on a single sizevar can violate
5785                 # a constraint
5786                 if not is_trivial and len(expr.free_symbols) == 1:
5787                     symbol = next(iter(expr.free_symbols))
5788                     source = symbol_to_source[symbol][0]
5789                     constraints = symbol_to_constraints[symbol]
5790                     for c in constraints:
5791                         if isinstance(c, StrictMinMaxConstraint):
5792                             var_with_range = (
5793                                 self._render_range_for_constraint_violation(source, c)
5794                             )
5795                             msg = (
5796                                 f"Not all values of {var_with_range} "
5797                                 f"satisfy the generated guard {py_printer.doprint(expr)}."
5798                             )
5799                             record_constraint_violation(
5800                                 c.warn_only, self._debug_name(source), msg
5801                             )
5802                         elif isinstance(c, RelaxedUnspecConstraint):
5803                             # This is fine, we allow guards here as long as it
5804                             # didn't constrain it to one value  (we don't
5805                             # actually know this; this depends on our
5806                             # ValueRanges reasoning capability)
5807                             pass
5808                         else:
5809                             raise AssertionError(f"unrecognized constraint {c}")
5810             except Exception:
5811                 self.log.warning("Failing guard allocated at %s", guard.sloc)
5812                 raise
5813 
5814         # First, issue all guards.
5815         # This removes all the checks that follow from bounds
5816         # We could simply emit those and also the bounds 2 <= size when necessary
5817         for guard in guards if guards is not None else self.guards:
5818             if (
5819                 self._maybe_evaluate_static(
5820                     guard.expr, axioms=(), size_oblivious=guard.size_oblivious
5821                 )
5822                 is not None
5823             ):
5824                 continue
5825             issue_guard(guard)
5826 
5827         # Because there are guards that export's constraint solver can suggest good fixes for, that we may have
5828         # deferred as runtime asserts, and that produce_guards() alone won't do anything with (e.g. divisiblity guards),
5829         # we want to send runtime asserts to export's constraint solver too. These will still stay in the graph as asserts,
5830         # but export's constraint solver can decide whether to do anything with them (i.e. raise an error and provide
5831         # suggested fixes, or decide it's out of scope and leave as a runtime assert in the graph).
5832         for ra in self.deferred_runtime_asserts.get(None, []):
5833             if self._maybe_evaluate_static(ra.expr, axioms=()) is not None:
5834                 continue
5835             expr = self.simplify(ra.expr)
5836             self.dim_constraints.add(expr)
5837 
5838         # 3. Every symbol must be within its value range (this handles 0/1
5839         # specialization too).
5840         for symbol, sources in symbol_to_source.items():
5841             r = self.var_to_range.get(symbol)
5842             if r is None:
5843                 continue
5844             vr_sloc = self.var_to_range_sloc[symbol]
5845 
5846             assert sources
5847             bounds = []
5848             rf = source_ref(sources[0])
5849             verbose_expr = ""
5850             if r.lower not in (-sympy.oo, -int_oo):
5851                 if any(is_dim(source) for source in sources):
5852                     self.dim_constraints.add(sympy.Ge(symbol, r.lower))
5853                 # Only print lower bound in simplified mode if it is not the
5854                 # default
5855                 if not _simplified or r.lower != self._default_value_range().lower:
5856                     bounds.append(sympy.Le(r.lower, symbol, evaluate=False))
5857                 verbose_expr = f"{r.lower} <= {rf}  # {vr_sloc.lower}"
5858             if r.upper not in (sympy.oo, int_oo):
5859                 if any(is_dim(source) for source in sources):
5860                     self.dim_constraints.add(sympy.Le(symbol, r.upper))
5861                 # nontrivial upper bound is always interesting
5862                 bounds.append(sympy.Le(symbol, r.upper, evaluate=False))
5863                 if verbose_expr:
5864                     verbose_expr = f"{r.lower} <= {rf} <= {r.upper}  # {vr_sloc.lower} and {vr_sloc.upper}"
5865                 else:
5866                     verbose_expr = f"{rf} <= {r.upper}  # {vr_sloc.upper}"
5867             if bounds:
5868                 bound = sympy.And(*bounds, evaluate=False)
5869 
5870                 for exprs, printer, lang in zip(all_exprs, printers, langs):
5871                     if lang == "verbose_python":
5872                         exprs.append(verbose_expr)
5873                     else:
5874                         exprs.append(printer.doprint(bound))
5875                 # NB: verbose_exprs are done above
5876 
5877                 # Check constraints
5878                 constraints = symbol_to_constraints[symbol]
5879                 for c in constraints:
5880                     if isinstance(c, StrictMinMaxConstraint):
5881                         # TODO: With int_oo, I think this condition is a noop
5882                         # now
5883                         if not (c.vr & self._default_value_range()).issubset(r):
5884                             source = sources[0]
5885 
5886                             expr = sympy.And(
5887                                 sympy.Le(r.lower, symbol), sympy.Le(symbol, r.upper)
5888                             )
5889                             guard_expr = py_printer.doprint(expr)
5890                             var_with_range = (
5891                                 self._render_range_for_constraint_violation(source, c)
5892                             )
5893                             msg = f"Not all values of {var_with_range} satisfy the generated guard {guard_expr}"
5894                             record_constraint_violation(
5895                                 c.warn_only,
5896                                 self._debug_name(source),
5897                                 msg,
5898                             )
5899             # We NaN specialize, which means similar to 0/1 specialization we
5900             # should assume that the float is NOT nan.  This is load bearing
5901             # if you have something like an equality guard, nan will play
5902             # merry hell with the reasoning.
5903             if symbol_is_type(symbol, SymT.FLOAT):
5904                 res = f"not math.isnan({py_printer.print_source(sources[0])})"
5905                 for exprs, printer, lang in zip(all_exprs, printers, langs):
5906                     if lang == "verbose_python":
5907                         exprs.append(
5908                             f"{res}  # implicit guard for float input due to NaN specialization in the framework"
5909                         )
5910                     elif lang == "python":
5911                         exprs.append(res)
5912                     elif lang == "cpp":
5913                         exprs.append(f"~std::isnan({printer.print_source(sources[0])})")
5914                     else:
5915                         raise NotImplementedError(f"Unimplemented for lang: {lang}")
5916 
5917         if constraint_violations:
5918             warn_msgs: list[str] = []
5919             error_msgs: list[str] = []
5920             debug_names = set()
5921             for warn_only, debug_name, msg_cb in constraint_violations:
5922                 if warn_only:
5923                     str_msg = f"  {len(warn_msgs) + 1}. {msg_cb()}"
5924                     warn_msgs.append(str_msg)
5925                 else:
5926                     str_msg = f"  - {msg_cb()}"
5927                     error_msgs.append(str_msg)
5928                     debug_names.add(debug_name)
5929             if len(error_msgs) > 0:
5930                 debug_names_str = ", ".join(sorted(debug_names))
5931                 err = "\n".join(error_msgs)
5932                 raise ConstraintViolationError(
5933                     f"Constraints violated ({debug_names_str})! "
5934                     'For more information, run with TORCH_LOGS="+dynamic".\n'
5935                     f"{err}"
5936                 )
5937             elif len(warn_msgs) > 0:
5938                 log.debug("%s Warning only constraints violated", len(warn_msgs))
5939 
5940         signpost_event(
5941             "dynamic",
5942             "produce_guards",
5943             {
5944                 **self.co_fields,
5945                 **self.counter,
5946                 "num_guards": len(all_exprs[0]),
5947                 "free_symbols": sum(1 for v in symbol_to_source.values() if v),
5948                 # The keys are meaningless from an aggregate perspective, so
5949                 # don't include them.  Biggest first.
5950                 "symbol_guard_counts": sorted(
5951                     self.symbol_guard_counter.values(), reverse=True
5952                 ),
5953             },
5954         )
5955 
5956         if self._translation_validation_enabled:
5957             from torch.fx.experimental.validator import PopulateValidator
5958 
5959             # Add all deferred runtime assertions; these are not technically
5960             # handled by produce_guards but we need to put them in the target
5961             # set
5962             for ras in self.deferred_runtime_asserts.values():
5963                 for ra in ras:
5964                     self._add_target_expr(ra.expr)
5965 
5966             # Add value range bound guards for all symbols with no trivial bounds.
5967             # Reason: '_maybe_evaluate_static' may eliminate guards based on the
5968             # refined value ranges.
5969             for sym, vr in self.var_to_range.items():
5970                 if vr.lower not in (-sympy.oo, -int_oo):
5971                     self._add_target_expr(sympy.Le(vr.lower, sym))
5972                 if vr.upper not in (sympy.oo, int_oo):
5973                     self._add_target_expr(sympy.Le(sym, vr.upper))
5974 
5975             # Before validating, populate the input of the validator with the
5976             # built FX graph.
5977             with fx_traceback.preserve_node_meta():
5978                 PopulateValidator(self.graph, self.validator).run()
5979 
5980         # Only run translation validation when we are not passing custom guards
5981         if guards is None:
5982             self._check_translation_validate()
5983 
5984         helpers: list[_ShapeGuardsHelper] = []
5985         for exprs, printer, lang in zip(all_exprs, printers, langs):
5986             if lang == "cpp":
5987                 assert isinstance(printer, _ShapeGuardCppPrinter)
5988                 helpers.append(_CppShapeGuardsHelper(exprs, printer.source_to_symbol))
5989             else:
5990                 helpers.append(_ShapeGuardsHelper(exprs))
5991         return helpers
5992 
5993     def produce_guards_expression(
5994         self,
5995         placeholders: Sequence[Union[SymInt, FakeTensor]],
5996         *,
5997         guards: Optional[list[ShapeGuard]] = None,
5998         ignore_static: bool = True,
5999     ) -> Optional[str]:
6000         """ 
6001         Expected to be used with evaluate_guards_expression(). Produces the guards 
6002         for the given placeholders and returns a string expression to be evaluated 
6003         by evaluate_guards_expression given concrete values for the placeholders. 
6004         """
6005         from torch._dynamo.source import LocalSource
6006 
6007         arg_names = [f"t{i}" for i in range(len(placeholders))]
6008         produced_guards = self.produce_guards(
6009             placeholders,
6010             [LocalSource(a) for a in arg_names],
6011             guards=guards,
6012             ignore_static=ignore_static,
6013         )
6014         if produced_guards:
6015             return " and ".join(produced_guards)
6016         return None
6017 
6018     def evaluate_symexpr(self, code: str) -> Union[int, float, bool]:
6019         """ 
6020         To be used by compile_fx to evaluate symexprs 
6021         """
6022         args = {str(e): val for e, val in self.var_to_val.items()}
6023         return eval(code, SYMPY_INTERP, args)
6024 
6025     def deserialize_symexpr(self, code: str) -> Union[SymInt, SymFloat, SymBool]:
6026         """ 
6027         To be used by compile_fx to deserialize symexprs 
6028         """
6029         args = {
6030             str(e): SymInt(SymNode(e, self, int, int(val), fx_node=None))
6031             for e, val in self.var_to_val.items()
6032         }
6033         return eval(code, SYMPY_INTERP, args)
6034 
6035     def evaluate_guards_expression(self, code: str, args: Sequence[object]) -> bool:
6036         """ 
6037         Expected to be used with produce_guards_expression(). Evaluates an expression 
6038         generated by produce_guards_expression for the given concrete args. 
6039         """
6040         arg_names = [f"t{i}" for i in range(len(args))]
6041         return eval(code, SYMPY_INTERP, {"L": dict(zip(arg_names, args))})
6042 
6043     def evaluate_guards_for_args(
6044         self,
6045         placeholders: Sequence[FakeTensor],
6046         args: Sequence[Tensor],
6047         *,
6048         ignore_static: bool = True,
6049     ) -> bool:
6050         """Generate guards for a graph's placeholder values and evaluate the guards with args"""
6051         code = self.produce_guards_expression(placeholders, ignore_static=ignore_static)
6052         if code:
6053             return self.evaluate_guards_expression(code, args)
6054         return True
6055 
6056     def get_pruned_guards(self, symints: Sequence[torch.SymInt]) -> list[ShapeGuard]:
6057         """ 
6058         Get a list of guards, but pruned so it only provides guards that 
6059         reference symints from the passed in input 
6060         """
6061         symints = {
6062             s.node.expr for s in symints if isinstance(s.node.expr, sympy.Symbol)
6063         }
6064         guards = [
6065             g for g in self.guards if all(s in symints for s in g.expr.free_symbols)
6066         ]
6067         return guards
6068 
6069     def bind_symbols(
6070         self, placeholders: Sequence[FakeTensor], args: Sequence[Tensor]
6071     ) -> dict[sympy.Symbol, int]:
6072         """ 
6073         Given a paired list of placeholders (fake tensors with 
6074         symbolic sizes) and concrete arguments (regular tensors 
6075         with real sizes), returns a dictionary mapping each 
6076         symbol to its real value.  So for example, if you 
6077         have a placeholder with size (s0, s1), binding 
6078         (2, 4) to it will give you {s0: 2, s1: 4}.  This is 
6079         not guaranteed to bind ALL symbols in the ShapeEnv; 
6080         we can't bind a symbol if it doesn't occur in any placeholder, 
6081         and symbols that already have replacements won't get bindings. 
6082  
6083         This is a little duplicative with evaluate_guards but 
6084         it's different enough that it seemed cleanest to make 
6085         another copy.  This assumes the guards are already checked, 
6086         though if it's cheap we'll check for shenanigans 
6087         """
6088         bindings: dict[sympy.Symbol, int] = {}
6089 
6090         def bind_symint(arg: object, val: object) -> None:
6091             if isinstance(val, SymInt):
6092                 assert isinstance(arg, int)
6093                 s = val.node.expr
6094 
6095                 if isinstance(s, sympy.Symbol):
6096                     if s in bindings:
6097                         assert bindings[s] == arg, f"{bindings[s]} != {arg}"
6098                     else:
6099                         bindings[s] = arg
6100                 elif isinstance(-s, sympy.Symbol):
6101                     if -s in bindings:
6102                         assert bindings[-s] == -arg, f"{bindings[-s]} != {-arg}"
6103                     else:
6104                         bindings[-s] = -arg
6105 
6106         for t, arg in zip(placeholders, args):
6107             if t is None:
6108                 continue
6109             if isinstance(t, SymInt):
6110                 bind_symint(arg, t)
6111                 continue
6112             assert isinstance(t, torch.Tensor)
6113             for i, s in enumerate(t.size()):
6114                 bind_symint(arg.size(i), s)
6115             for i, s in enumerate(t.stride()):
6116                 bind_symint(arg.stride(i), s)
6117             bind_symint(arg.storage_offset(), t.storage_offset())
6118 
6119         return bindings
6120 
6121     def get_nontrivial_guards(self) -> list[SympyBoolean]:
6122         """Returns a list of guard expressions that aren't statically known (i.e. not trivial)"""
6123         return [
6124             self.simplify(guard.expr)
6125             for guard in self.guards
6126             if self._maybe_evaluate_static(
6127                 guard.expr, axioms=(), size_oblivious=guard.size_oblivious
6128             )
6129             is None
6130         ]
6131 
6132     def format_guards(self, verbose: bool = False) -> str:
6133         """Format this shape env's guard expressions with optional traceback info if verbose"""
6134 
6135         return "\n".join(
6136             f" - {guard.expr}{' ' + str(guard.sloc) if verbose else ''}"
6137             for guard in self.guards
6138         )
6139 
6140     def bound_sympy(
6141         self, expr: sympy.Expr, size_oblivious: bool = False
6142     ) -> ValueRanges:
6143         """Given a sympy expression, computes a ValueRanges bound for what values it can be"""
6144         # TODO: maybe it's guaranteed x in is var_to_range?
6145         var_to_range = {x: self.var_to_range.get(x, None) for x in expr.free_symbols}
6146         if size_oblivious:
6147             # Clamp values of size-like variables
6148             # NB: discarding the old upper bound in intentional, per
6149             # https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/123675
6150             for x in self.size_like & var_to_range.keys():
6151                 if var_to_range[x] is not None:
6152                     # NB: do NOT set upper to 2 ** 48, we're using this solely
6153                     # to determine if we can do size-like replacement, the
6154                     # upper bound is irrelevant here
6155                     var_to_range[x] = ValueRanges(2, int_oo)
6156         return bound_sympy(expr, var_to_range)  # type: ignore[arg-type]
6157 
6158     @_lru_cache
6159     def get_axioms(
6160         self,
6161         symbols: Optional[tuple[sympy.Symbol]] = None,
6162         compute_hint: bool = False,
6163     ) -> tuple[SympyBoolean, ...]:
6164         """ 
6165         Given the symbols in an expression, it returns all the runtime asserts that have those symbols 
6166         concatenated with all the guards. 
6167         If symbols is None, it returns all the runtime asserts (and all the guards) 
6168         """
6169         if symbols is None:
6170             runtime_asserts = (
6171                 r.expr for rs in self.deferred_runtime_asserts.values() for r in rs
6172             )
6173         else:
6174             runtime_asserts = (
6175                 r.expr
6176                 for s in symbols
6177                 if s not in self.var_to_val
6178                 for r in self.deferred_runtime_asserts.get(s, ())
6179             )
6180         guards: Iterator[SympyBoolean] = (g.expr for g in self.guards)
6181         axioms: Iterator[SympyBoolean] = itertools.chain(guards, runtime_asserts)
6182         if compute_hint:
6183             axioms = (
6184                 canonicalize_bool_expr(a.xreplace(self.var_to_val)) for a in axioms
6185             )
6186         return tuple(dict.fromkeys(axioms).keys())
6187 
6188     @lru_cache(None)
6189     def get_implications(
6190         self, e: SympyBoolean
6191     ) -> tuple[tuple[SympyBoolean, sympy.logic.boolalg.BooleanAtom], ...]:
6192         """Given a expression, it returns a list of predicates that follow from it"""
6193         equiv: dict[SympyBoolean, sympy.logic.boolalg.BooleanAtom] = {}
6194 
6195         def add_expr(expr: SympyBoolean) -> None:
6196             expr = canonicalize_bool_expr(expr)
6197             if isinstance(expr, (sympy.Eq, sympy.Ne)):
6198                 # No need to canonicalize
6199                 # TODO We could further canonicalize Eq ordering the lhs and rhs somehow
6200                 # With this, we could remove the need for the commutativity part
6201                 opposite = sympy.Eq if isinstance(expr, sympy.Ne) else sympy.Ne
6202                 # Commutativity of == and !=
6203                 equiv[type(expr)(expr.lhs, expr.rhs, evaluate=False)] = sympy.true
6204                 equiv[type(expr)(expr.rhs, expr.lhs, evaluate=False)] = sympy.true
6205                 equiv[opposite(expr.lhs, expr.rhs, evaluate=False)] = sympy.false
6206                 equiv[opposite(expr.rhs, expr.lhs, evaluate=False)] = sympy.false
6207             else:
6208                 # Expr and negation
6209                 equiv[expr] = sympy.true
6210                 # we do not pass evaluate=False like others on purpose here!
6211                 # we want not(a<b) to be a>=b and not ~(a<b).
6212                 equiv[canonicalize_bool_expr(sympy.Not(expr))] = sympy.false
6213 
6214         add_expr(e)
6215         # Other relational expressions this expression implies
6216         if isinstance(e, sympy.Eq):
6217             add_expr(sympy.Le(e.lhs, e.rhs, evaluate=False))
6218             add_expr(sympy.Ge(e.lhs, e.rhs, evaluate=False))
6219         elif isinstance(e, sympy.Lt):
6220             add_expr(sympy.Le(e.lhs, e.rhs, evaluate=False))
6221             add_expr(sympy.Ne(e.lhs, e.rhs, evaluate=False))
6222             if e.lhs.is_integer and e.rhs.is_integer:  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
6223                 add_expr(sympy.Le(e.lhs, e.rhs - 1, evaluate=False))
6224         elif isinstance(e, sympy.Le):
6225             add_expr(sympy.Lt(e.lhs, e.rhs + 1, evaluate=False))
6226 
6227         return tuple(equiv.items())
6228 
6229     @_lru_cache
6230     def _maybe_evaluate_static(
6231         self,
6232         expr: sympy.Basic,
6233         *,
6234         unbacked_only: bool = False,
6235         compute_hint: bool = False,
6236         size_oblivious: bool = False,
6237         axioms: Optional[tuple[SympyBoolean]] = None,
6238         var_to_range: Optional[tuple[tuple[sympy.Symbol, ValueRanges]]] = None,
6239     ) -> Optional[sympy.Basic]:
6240         """ 
6241         Tries to evaluate expr without introducing guards 
6242  
6243         If unbacked_only == True, then we only do substitutions on 
6244         unbacked SymInts (leaving regular hinted integers alone).  This could 
6245         result in an expression that still contains backed SymInts, which you 
6246         could then potentially guard on. 
6247  
6248         Use compute_hint == True if you are trying to compute a non-binding 
6249         hint for the particular hint values of backed and unbacked SymInts, 
6250         e.g., if s0 happens to be 3 this run, compute_hint will subsitute s0 with 3. 
6251         """
6252 
6253         # axioms with compute hint NYE
6254         assert not compute_hint or not axioms
6255         expr = self.simplify(expr, size_oblivious)
6256 
6257         if compute_hint:
6258             expr = expr.xreplace(self.var_to_val).xreplace(self.unbacked_var_to_val)
6259 
6260         expr = canonicalize_bool_expr(expr)
6261 
6262         def resimplify_floor_div(axioms: dict[sympy.Expr, sympy.Expr]) -> None:
6263             if not self._resimplify_floor_div_axioms:
6264                 return
6265             self._resimplify_floor_div_axioms = False
6266             new_items = {}
6267             for k, v in axioms.items():
6268                 # A FloorDiv in implications could have became CleanDiv at this point, due to new facts
6269                 # to the shapeEnv. This handles such issue but its not ideal. This is the only expression
6270                 # simplification that depends on the global state of shape env.
6271                 # TODO try to get rid of CleanDiv since it breaks the invariant thats simplifications of sympy
6272                 # expressions only depend on the expression itself.
6273                 if k.has(FloorDiv):
6274                     new_items.update({self.simplify(k): v})
6275             axioms.update(new_items)
6276 
6277         # Pattern matching
6278         if axioms is None:
6279             resimplify_floor_div(self.axioms)
6280             subst = self.axioms
6281         else:
6282             subst = {}
6283             for e in axioms:
6284                 if e.free_symbols.issubset(expr.free_symbols):
6285                     subst.update(dict(self.get_implications(self.simplify(e))))
6286 
6287             resimplify_floor_div(subst)
6288 
6289         expr = expr.xreplace(subst)
6290         # TODO: compute hint might have gotten broken here
6291 
6292         fs = expr.free_symbols
6293 
6294         if not fs and (expr.is_number or expr.is_Boolean):
6295             return expr
6296 
6297         if var_to_range is None:
6298             var_ranges = self.var_to_range
6299         else:
6300             var_ranges = dict(var_to_range)
6301 
6302         symbol_info = tuple(
6303             _SymbolInfo(
6304                 s,
6305                 var_ranges.get(s),
6306                 self.var_to_val.get(s),
6307                 s in self.size_like,
6308             )
6309             for s in sorted(fs, key=str)  # TODO: speed up sort?
6310         )
6311 
6312         r = _maybe_evaluate_static_worker(
6313             expr, symbol_info, unbacked_only, size_oblivious
6314         )
6315         return r
6316 
6317     @_lru_cache
6318     def replace(self, expr: _SympyT) -> _SympyT:
6319         """ 
6320         Apply symbol replacements to any symbols in the given expression. 
6321         """
6322         replacements = {}
6323         for s in expr.free_symbols:
6324             r = self._find(s)
6325 
6326             # Micro-optimization: only do replacements if r and s are different
6327             # Otherwise, xreplace is not a no-op and will trigger expensive
6328             # assumption queries if expr has a relational node.
6329             if not r.is_Symbol or r != s:
6330                 replacements[s] = r
6331         if replacements:
6332             return safe_expand(expr.xreplace(replacements))
6333         else:
6334             return expr
6335 
6336     @_lru_cache
6337     def _update_divisible(self) -> None:
6338         new_divisible = set()
6339         for k in self.divisible:
6340             res = self.replace(k)
6341             if not res.is_number:
6342                 new_divisible.add(k)
6343 
6344         self.divisible = new_divisible
6345         self._update_version_counter()
6346 
6347     @_lru_cache
6348     def simplify(self, expr: _SympyT, size_oblivious: bool = False) -> _SympyT:
6349         """Use known constraints and replacements to simplify the given expr"""
6350         expr = safe_expand(expr)
6351         expr = self.replace(expr)
6352 
6353         if size_oblivious and (expr.has(Max) or expr.has(Min)):  # type: ignore[has-type]
6354             min_max_replacements = {}
6355             for atom in (*expr.atoms(Max), *expr.atoms(Min)):  # type: ignore[has-type]
6356                 if len(atom.args) > 2:
6357                     continue
6358                 a, b = atom.args
6359                 if b == 1 or b == 0:
6360                     a, b = b, a
6361                 if a == 1 or a == 0:
6362                     vr = self.bound_sympy(b, size_oblivious=True)
6363                     if vr.lower >= a:
6364                         min_max_replacements[atom] = b if atom.func is Max else a
6365                     elif vr.upper <= a:
6366                         min_max_replacements[atom] = a if atom.func is Max else b
6367             if min_max_replacements:
6368                 expr = expr.xreplace(min_max_replacements)
6369 
6370         if expr.has(TruncToInt):
6371             trunc_replacements = {}
6372             for atom in expr.atoms(TruncToInt):
6373                 if isinstance(atom.args[0], IntTrueDiv):
6374                     base, divisor = atom.args[0].args
6375                     if base % divisor == 0:
6376                         trunc_replacements[atom] = base // divisor
6377             if trunc_replacements:
6378                 expr = expr.xreplace(trunc_replacements)
6379 
6380         # TODO it would seem that this pass is not necessary given the
6381         # below replacement of // with /, but for nested FloorDivs
6382         # the non-recursive replacement doesn't work, and
6383         # recursive makes it hard to look up divisibility,
6384         # because existing divisibility info has FloorDiv in it, not /
6385         # for now just do a separate pass to catch common nested case
6386         if expr.has(FloorDiv):
6387             self._update_divisible()
6388             div_replacements = {}
6389             for atom in expr.atoms(FloorDiv):
6390                 base, divisor = atom.args
6391                 if isinstance(divisor, FloorDiv):
6392                     base1, divisor1 = divisor.args
6393                     if (
6394                         self.replace(Mod(base, divisor)) in self.divisible
6395                         and base == base1
6396                         and self.replace(Mod(base1, divisor1)) in self.divisible
6397                     ):
6398                         div_replacements[atom] = divisor1
6399             if div_replacements:
6400                 expr = expr.xreplace(div_replacements)
6401                 expr = safe_expand(expr)
6402         if expr.has(FloorDiv):
6403             div_replacements = {}
6404             pows = expr.atoms(sympy.Pow)
6405             rationals = expr.atoms(sympy.Rational).difference(expr.atoms(sympy.Integer))
6406             for fd in expr.atoms(FloorDiv):
6407                 base, divisor = fd.args
6408                 if self.replace(Mod(base, divisor)) in self.divisible:
6409                     div_replacements[fd] = CleanDiv(base, divisor)
6410             if div_replacements:
6411                 new_expr = expr.xreplace(div_replacements)
6412                 new_expr = safe_expand(new_expr)
6413                 new_pows = new_expr.atoms(sympy.Pow)
6414                 new_rationals = new_expr.atoms(sympy.Rational).difference(
6415                     new_expr.atoms(sympy.Integer)
6416                 )
6417                 # divisions simplified away
6418                 if new_pows.issubset(pows) and new_rationals.issubset(rationals):
6419                     expr = new_expr
6420         return expr
6421 
6422     # TODO: overload for allow_none literal
6423     @lru_cache(256)
6424     def size_hint(
6425         self, expr: sympy.Basic, *, allow_none: bool = False
6426     ) -> Optional[sympy.Basic]:
6427         """ 
6428         Gets a size hint for a given expression from the underlying shapes we had. 
6429         Does not introduce a guard, so only use this when you can guarantee that 
6430         your code is still valid for arbitrary shapes (such as optimization decisions) 
6431         """
6432         result_expr = safe_expand(expr).xreplace(self.var_to_val)
6433         if not result_expr.is_number:
6434             from torch.utils._sympy.singleton_int import SingletonInt
6435 
6436             if isinstance(result_expr, SingletonInt):
6437                 return None
6438             r = self._maybe_evaluate_static(result_expr, compute_hint=True)
6439             if r is not None:
6440                 return r
6441             if allow_none:
6442                 return None
6443 
6444             if self.oblivious_var_to_val:
6445                 # See https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/137100#issuecomment-2495778113
6446                 correct_hint = result_expr.xreplace(self.oblivious_var_to_val)
6447                 counterfactual_hint = result_expr.xreplace(
6448                     {k: max(v, 2) for k, v in self.oblivious_var_to_val.items()}
6449                 )
6450                 if (
6451                     not correct_hint.free_symbols
6452                     and not counterfactual_hint.free_symbols
6453                 ):
6454                     if correct_hint == counterfactual_hint:
6455                         log.info("oblivious_size hit %s -> %s", expr, correct_hint)
6456                         return correct_hint
6457                     else:
6458                         log.info(
6459                             "oblivious_size counterfactual failed %s -> %s != %s",
6460                             expr,
6461                             correct_hint,
6462                             counterfactual_hint,
6463                         )
6464                 else:
6465                     log.info(
6466                         "oblivious_size miss %s -> %s (counterfactual: %s)",
6467                         expr,
6468                         correct_hint,
6469                         counterfactual_hint,
6470                     )
6471 
6472             if self.unbacked_var_to_val:
6473                 unsound_expr = result_expr.xreplace(self.unbacked_var_to_val)
6474                 if not unsound_expr.free_symbols:
6475                     log.warning(
6476                         "propagate_real_tensors size_hint(%s) -> %s", expr, unsound_expr
6477                     )
6478                     trace_structured(
6479                         "propagate_real_tensors",
6480                         metadata_fn=lambda: {
6481                             "expr": repr(expr),
6482                             "result": repr(unsound_expr),
6483                             "stack": structured.from_traceback(
6484                                 CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1).summary()
6485                             ),
6486                         },
6487                     )
6488                     self.guard_or_defer_runtime_assert(
6489                         sympy.Eq(result_expr, unsound_expr),
6490                         f"propagate_real_tensors: {result_expr} == {unsound_expr}",
6491                     )
6492                     return unsound_expr
6493 
6494             raise self._make_data_dependent_error(result_expr, expr)
6495         return result_expr
6496 
6497     # NB: keep in sync with size_hint
6498     @lru_cache(256)
6499     def has_hint(self, expr: sympy.Expr) -> bool:
6500         result_expr = safe_expand(expr).xreplace(self.var_to_val)
6501         return (
6502             result_expr.is_number
6503             or self._maybe_evaluate_static(result_expr) is not None
6504         )
6505 
6506     def _make_data_dependent_error(
6507         self,
6508         expr: sympy.Basic,
6509         unhinted_expr: sympy.Basic,
6510         *,
6511         size_oblivious_result: Optional[sympy.Basic] = None,
6512         expr_sym_node_id: Optional[int] = None,
6513     ) -> GuardOnDataDependentSymNode:
6514         # TODO: in a Dynamo context, having user code, and having the
6515         # name of the local, will be much better
6516         size_like_symbols = []
6517         for s in expr.free_symbols:
6518             stacktrace = "".join(self.var_to_stack[s].format())
6519             self.log.debug(
6520                 "Data dependent variable '%s' allocated at:\n%s", s, stacktrace
6521             )
6522             if s in self.size_like:
6523                 size_like_symbols.append(s)
6524         size_oblivious_result_msg = ""
6525         if size_oblivious_result is not None:
6526             size_oblivious_result_msg = (
6527                 f"ATTENTION: guard_size_oblivious would fix the error, evaluating expression to {size_oblivious_result}.\n"
6528                 "Maybe you need to add guard_size_oblivious to framework code, see doc below for more guidance.\n\n"
6529             )
6530         sloc, maybe_extra_debug = self._get_stack_summary(True)
6531         if expr.is_integer:  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
6532             desc = (
6533                 "Could not extract specialized integer from data-dependent expression"
6534             )
6535         else:
6536             desc = "Could not guard on data-dependent expression"
6537         msg = (
6538             f"{desc} {expr} (unhinted: {unhinted_expr}).  "
6539             f"(Size-like symbols: {', '.join(map(str, size_like_symbols)) or 'none'})\n\n"
6540             f"{size_oblivious_result_msg}"
6541             f"Caused by: {sloc}\n"
6542             'For more information, run with TORCH_LOGS="dynamic"\n'
6543             "For extended logs when we create symbols, also add "
6544             f'TORCHDYNAMO_EXTENDED_DEBUG_CREATE_SYMBOL="{",".join(map(str, expr.free_symbols))}"\n'
6545             "If you suspect the guard was triggered from C++, add TORCHDYNAMO_EXTENDED_DEBUG_CPP=1\n"
6546             "For more debugging help, see "
6547             "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HSuTTVvYH1pTew89Rtpeu84Ht3nQEFTYhAX3Ypa_xJs/edit?usp=sharing\n"
6548             + maybe_extra_debug
6549             # TODO: Help text about how to use our runtime tests to fix this
6550             # problem
6551         )
6552 
6553         dtrace_structured(
6554             "guard_on_data_dependent_error",
6555             metadata_fn=lambda: {
6556                 "expr": repr(expr),
6557                 "unhinted_expr": repr(unhinted_expr),
6558                 "expr_id": self._expr_sym_node_id,
6559                 "stack": structured.from_traceback(
6560                     CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1).summary()
6561                 ),
6562             },
6563         )
6564         return GuardOnDataDependentSymNode(expr, msg)
6565 
6566     def _update_var_to_range(
6567         self,
6568         symbol: sympy.Symbol,
6569         vr: ValueRanges,
6570         vr_sloc: Optional[ValueRangesSLoc] = None,
6571         *,
6572         is_constraint: bool = False,
6573     ) -> None:
6574         lower, upper = vr.lower, vr.upper
6575 
6576         # If we have a size-like unbacked SymInt, refuse to refine the range to be
6577         # less than two.  This is because when we intersect this range
6578         # with [2, inf] for size oblivious tests, the range would be
6579         # unsatisfiable.  In other words, once you have a size-like
6580         # unbacked SymInt, we can never learn that it is exactly zero or one,
6581         # because we would now give inconsistent results for all size
6582         # oblivous tests!
6583         if upper < 2 and symbol in self.size_like:
6584             vr = ValueRanges(lower, 2)
6585 
6586         # Updates the range and the guards corresponding to each bound of the symbol.
6587         if symbol not in self.var_to_range:
6588             self.log.debug("_update_var_to_range %s = %s (new)", symbol, vr)
6589             self.var_to_range[symbol] = vr
6590             if vr_sloc is None:
6591                 sloc = self._get_sloc()
6592                 vr_sloc = ValueRangesSLoc(sloc, sloc)
6593             self.var_to_range_sloc[symbol] = vr_sloc
6594         else:
6595             old = self.var_to_range[symbol]
6596             new = old & vr
6597             if new != old:
6598                 if vr_sloc is None:
6599                     sloc = self._get_sloc()
6600                     vr_sloc = ValueRangesSLoc(sloc, sloc)
6601                 if new.lower != old.lower:
6602                     self.var_to_range_sloc[symbol].lower = vr_sloc.lower
6603                 if new.upper != old.upper:
6604                     self.var_to_range_sloc[symbol].upper = vr_sloc.upper
6605                 self.var_to_range[symbol] = new
6606                 self.log.debug("_update_var_to_range %s = %s (update)", symbol, new)
6607 
6608         if (v := self.var_to_val.get(symbol)) is not None:
6609             r = self.var_to_range[symbol]
6610             if v not in r:
6611                 # For constraint failure, delay this for later
6612                 # TODO: Rework all of this, the constraint logic is very
6613                 # duplicative with regular reasoning
6614                 if not is_constraint:
6615                     assert v in r, f"{v} not in {r}"
6616 
6617     def _set_replacement(self, a: sympy.Symbol, tgt: sympy.Expr, msg: str) -> None:
6618         """ 
6619         Adds or updates a replacement for a symbol. 
6620         Use this instead of `self.replacements[a] = tgt`. 
6621         """
6622         if tgt == self.replacements.get(a, None):
6623             return
6624 
6625         if a in tgt.free_symbols:
6626             return
6627 
6628         # Precondition: a == tgt
6629         assert isinstance(a, sympy.Symbol)
6630 
6631         if (
6632             self.allow_complex_guards_as_runtime_asserts
6633             and not _is_supported_equivalence(tgt)
6634         ):
6635             return  # continuing leads to placeholder shapes having complex expressions that we can't resolve
6636 
6637         # Handles nested tensor symbolic variables which don't have
6638         # var_to_range bounds
6639         tgt_bound = None
6640         if a in self.var_to_range:
6641             src_bound = self.var_to_range[a]
6642 
6643             # First, refine the value range of a based on the computed value range
6644             # of tgt.  This is always OK to do, even if we decide not to do the
6645             # substitution in the end.  This might be a no-op, if a already has
6646             # a tighter bound
6647             tgt_bound = self.bound_sympy(tgt)
6648             self._update_var_to_range(a, tgt_bound)
6649 
6650             # Next, check if we can update the range of free symbols in tgt
6651             # based on the range in a. But only do it if:
6652             #  - the source bound non-trivially improves over what we get out of
6653             #    the existing bounds.
6654             #  - the replacement is univariate and we can invert the tgt expression
6655             if not tgt_bound.issubset(src_bound) and len(tgt.free_symbols) == 1:
6656                 b = next(iter(tgt.free_symbols))
6657                 # Try to invert the equality
6658                 r = try_solve(sympy.Eq(a, tgt), b, floordiv_inequality=False)
6659                 if r is not None:
6660                     self.log.debug(
6661                         "set_replacement: solve for %s in %s == %s gives %s",
6662                         b,
6663                         a,
6664                         tgt,
6665                         r,
6666                     )
6667                     # The solution here can be non-integral, for example, if
6668                     # we have s0 = 2*s1, then s1 = s0/2.  What we would like
6669                     # to do is calculated the bounds in arbitrary precision,
6670                     # and then requantize the bound to integers when we are
6671                     # done.
6672                     rat_b_bound = self.bound_sympy(r[1])
6673                     b_bound = ValueRanges(
6674                         CeilToInt(rat_b_bound.lower), FloorToInt(rat_b_bound.upper)
6675                     )
6676                     self._update_var_to_range(b, b_bound, self.var_to_range_sloc[a])
6677                     tgt_bound = self.bound_sympy(tgt)
6678                     assert tgt_bound.issubset(src_bound), (
6679                         f"{tgt_bound=} not a subset of {src_bound=}"
6680                     )
6681 
6682             # TODO: Should we propagate size-like-ness?
6683             #
6684             # Pros: if u0 is size-like, intuitively u0 == u1 should cause u1
6685             # to become size-like.
6686             #
6687             # Cons: if u0 is size-like, what about u0 - 1 == u1?  You CAN'T
6688             # propagate in this case, because what if u0 == 0, then u1 is negative
6689             # and clearly isn't a size.  So, at minimum, any f(x) whose value
6690             # range isn't [0, inf] given x in [0, inf] cannot propagate
6691             # size-like-ness.  But there are many situations where you could
6692             # imagine u1 is going to be size-like and actually you just didn't
6693             # have a refined enough value range on u0.  Since even innocuous
6694             # looking arithmetic operations can destroy size-like-ness, it's
6695             # best to not propagate it at all and force the user to annotate it
6696             # as necessary.
6697             #
6698             # Compromise: we preserve size-like-ness only for exact equality
6699             # and nothing else.
6700             if a in self.size_like and isinstance(tgt, sympy.Symbol):
6701                 self.size_like.add(tgt)
6702             elif isinstance(tgt, sympy.Symbol) and tgt in self.size_like:
6703                 self.size_like.add(a)
6704 
6705             # Now, decide if we will do the substitution.
6706             #
6707             #  - If the source has a non-trivial range, only substitute if
6708             #    we preserve this range.  Note that we may have propagated
6709             #    the src_range to free variables in tgt when tgt is univariate
6710             #    and we could find an inverse, which helps us achieve this.
6711             #    This ensures we never "forget" about user defined ranges,
6712             #    even if they end up being defined on composite formulas
6713             #    like s0 + s1.
6714             #
6715             #  - If the variable is unbacked, only substitute if the substitution
6716             #    would preserve the bounds also under size-like-ness conditions.
6717 
6718             if not tgt_bound.issubset(src_bound):
6719                 self.log.debug(
6720                     "skipped set_replacement %s = %s (%s) [%s not subset of %s]",
6721                     a,
6722                     tgt,
6723                     msg,
6724                     tgt_bound,
6725                     src_bound,
6726                 )
6727                 return
6728             elif a in self.size_like:
6729                 tgt_bound_so = self.bound_sympy(tgt, size_oblivious=True)
6730                 src_bound_so = self.bound_sympy(a, size_oblivious=True)
6731                 if not tgt_bound_so.issubset(src_bound_so):
6732                     self.log.debug(
6733                         "skipped set_replacement %s = %s (%s) "
6734                         "[%s not subset of %s (size-oblivious conditions)]",
6735                         a,
6736                         tgt,
6737                         msg,
6738                         tgt_bound_so,
6739                         src_bound_so,
6740                     )
6741                     return
6742 
6743         if isinstance(tgt, (sympy.Integer, sympy.Float)):
6744             # specializing to a constant, which is likely unexpected (unless
6745             # you specified dynamic=True)
6746 
6747             user_tb = TracingContext.extract_stack()
6748             trace_structured(
6749                 "symbolic_shape_specialization",
6750                 metadata_fn=lambda: {
6751                     "symbol": repr(a),
6752                     "sources": [s.name() for s in self.var_to_sources.get(a, [])],
6753                     "value": repr(tgt),
6754                     "reason": msg,
6755                     "stack": structured.from_traceback(
6756                         CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1).summary()
6757                     ),
6758                     "user_stack": (
6759                         structured.from_traceback(user_tb) if user_tb else None
6760                     ),
6761                 },
6762             )
6763 
6764             for source in self.var_to_sources.get(a, []):
6765                 if user_tb:
6766                     self.user_specialization_stacks[source] = user_tb
6767                 self.framework_specialization_stacks[source] = (
6768                     CapturedTraceback.extract(cpp=True)
6769                 )
6770 
6771             if config.print_specializations:
6772                 self.log.warning(
6773                     "Specializing %s to %s", self.var_to_sources[a][0].name(), tgt
6774                 )
6775                 self.log.debug("SPECIALIZATION", stack_info=True)
6776         log.info("set_replacement %s = %s (%s) %s", a, tgt, msg, tgt_bound)
6777         self.replacements[a] = tgt
6778         # NB: the replacement may get refined, but the user will find the
6779         # FIRST one most useful (TODO: Maybe we could consider tracking all of
6780         # them)
6781         if a not in self.replacements_slocs:
6782             self.replacements_slocs[a] = self._get_sloc()
6783         self._update_version_counter()
6784 
6785         # When specializing 'a == tgt', the equality should be also conveyed to
6786         # Z3, in case an expression uses 'a'.
6787         self._add_target_expr(sympy.Eq(a, tgt, evaluate=False))
6788 
6789     def _add_divisible(self, expr: sympy.Expr) -> None:
6790         self.divisible.add(expr)
6791         self._update_version_counter()
6792 
6793     @_lru_cache
6794     @record_shapeenv_event()
6795     def _find(self, a: sympy.Symbol) -> sympy.Expr:
6796         """ 
6797         Implements a DSU-like algorithm to find the variable that represents a 
6798         Also handles transitive non-identity replacements. 
6799  
6800         a: b + c 
6801         c: d 
6802         """
6803         if a not in self.replacements:
6804             return a
6805         res = self.replacements[a]
6806         cur_replace = {s: self._find(s) for s in res.free_symbols}
6807         replaced, changed = self.replacements[a]._xreplace(cur_replace)
6808         if changed:
6809             self._set_replacement(a, replaced, "find")
6810         return self.replacements[a]
6811 
6812     @lru_cache(256)
6813     def _maybe_guard_rel(self, expr: sympy.Expr) -> None:
6814         """
