6815         The relational guard is guarded to be true.  Use this information to 
6816         simplify shapes (i.e. a == b or a % 5 == 0) 
6817         """
6818         if isinstance(expr, sympy.And):
6819             for arg in expr.args:
6820                 self._maybe_guard_rel(arg)
6821             return
6822         elif not isinstance(expr, sympy.Rel):
6823             log.warning(
6824                 "_maybe_guard_rel() was called on non-relation expression %s", expr
6825             )
6826             return
6827 
6828         # A good example of what goes wrong if you don't do this is
6829         # python test/functorch/test_aotdispatch.py -k
6830         # test_aot_autograd_symbolic_module_exhaustive_nn_LazyConv3d_cpu_float32
6831         if isinstance(expr, sympy.Ne):
6832             return
6833 
6834         free = list(expr.free_symbols)
6835 
6836         assert len(free) > 0, (
6837             f"The expression should not be static by this point: {expr}"
6838         )
6839         # In case of really gnarly expression, we don't blow up
6840         if len(free) > 5:
6841             return
6842 
6843         # Prioritize unbacked symints for solving by ordering them last.
6844         # Prefer to simplify out lexicographically higher symbols (i.e. simplify out s4 over s3).
6845         #   (NB: this unfortunately isn't strictly equivalent to simplifying out newer symbols)
6846         # Prefer to simplify out symbols with ephemeral sources.
6847         def _smart_symbol_sort(x: sympy.Symbol) -> tuple[int, int, str]:
6848             has_only_ephemeral_sources = x in self.var_to_sources and all(
6849                 s.is_ephemeral() for s in self.var_to_sources[x]
6850             )
6851             # NB: size_hint is int, not sympy.Expr, do not use int_oo here
6852             hint_size = self.size_hint(x, allow_none=True)
6853             if hint_size is None:
6854                 size = sys.maxsize
6855             elif symbol_is_type(x, SymT.SIZE):
6856                 assert isinstance(hint_size, sympy.Expr)
6857                 size = int(hint_size)
6858             else:
6859                 size = sys.maxsize
6860             name = x.name
6861             # 1 puts ephemeral sourced symbols first when sorting in reverse
6862             return (1 if has_only_ephemeral_sources else 0, size, name)
6863 
6864         free = sorted(free, key=_smart_symbol_sort, reverse=True)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
6865         lhs = expr.lhs
6866         rhs = expr.rhs
6867 
6868         self._refine_ranges(expr)
6869 
6870         # The rest of this stuff is for equality only
6871         if not isinstance(expr, sympy.Eq):
6872             return
6873 
6874         if not expr.has(Mod):
6875             try:
6876                 floor_div_atoms = lhs.atoms(FloorDiv).union(rhs.atoms(FloorDiv))
6877                 if len(floor_div_atoms) > 0 and any(
6878                     a.divisor != 1 for a in floor_div_atoms
6879                 ):
6880                     raise NotImplementedError
6881 
6882                 # Never replace unbacked symbols with other unbacked symbols.
6883                 # This is error prone because you can cause references to
6884                 # unbacked symbols to time travel backwards.  E.g.,
6885                 #
6886                 # u1 = x.item()
6887                 # ... use of u1 ...
6888                 # u2 = y.item()
6889                 # u3 = z.item()
6890                 # torch._check(u1 == u2 + u3)
6891                 #
6892                 # If you replace u1 with u2 + u3, then the use of u1 now
6893                 # references u2 and u3 prior to them actually being bound at
6894                 # runtime.  It's pretty inconvenient to setup control
6895                 # dependencies for substitutions, so ban it entirely.
6896                 def trivial_solve(lhs: sympy.Expr, rhs: sympy.Expr) -> bool:
6897                     if isinstance(lhs, sympy.Symbol):
6898                         if free_unbacked_symbols(lhs) and not free_unbacked_symbols(
6899                             rhs
6900                         ):
6901                             return True
6902                         if symbol_is_type(lhs, SymT.FLOAT):
6903                             return True
6904                         # TODO: Maybe trivial solutions for int should also be
6905                         # done?
6906                     return False
6907 
6908                 # short-circuit when no solving is needed
6909                 if trivial_solve(lhs, rhs):
6910                     self._set_replacement(lhs, self._find(rhs), "trivial_lhs")
6911                 elif trivial_solve(rhs, lhs):
6912                     self._set_replacement(rhs, self._find(lhs), "trivial_rhs")
6913                 else:
6914                     r = try_solve(expr, free[0], floordiv_inequality=False)
6915                     if r is not None and all(
6916                         t.is_integer for t in sympy.preorder_traversal(r[1])
6917                     ):
6918                         new_var = self._find(r[1])
6919                         ok = len(free_unbacked_symbols(new_var)) == 0
6920                         if ok:
6921                             self._set_replacement(free[0], new_var, "solve")
6922             except NotImplementedError:
6923                 pass
6924         if expr.has(Mod):
6925             mod_expr = next(iter(expr.atoms(Mod)))
6926             try:
6927                 r = try_solve(expr, mod_expr, floordiv_inequality=False)
6928                 if r is not None and r[1] == 0:
6929                     self._add_divisible(mod_expr)
6930                     # This is a little bit of extra logic to make things like
6931                     # torch.empty(i0, q).view(c, -1, q) work out
6932                     p, q = mod_expr.args
6933                     if (
6934                         isinstance(q, sympy.Number)
6935                         and isinstance(p, sympy.Mul)
6936                         and len(p.args) == 2
6937                     ):
6938                         c, i0 = p.args
6939                         # Given Mod(c * i0, q) == 0
6940                         if (
6941                             isinstance(c, sympy.Number)
6942                             and isinstance(i0, sympy.Symbol)
6943                             and self.is_unbacked_symint(i0)
6944                         ):
6945                             # We have Mod(i0, q / c) == 0, which means we can
6946                             # rewrite i0 as (q / gcd(q, c)) * i1
6947                             d = q / sympy.gcd(q, c)  # TODO: CleanDiv?
6948                             i1 = self.create_unbacked_symint().node.expr
6949                             # Propagate the value ranges.  It doesn't really
6950                             # matter if we use truediv or floordiv, because we
6951                             # have established divisibility.
6952                             self._update_var_to_range(
6953                                 i1,
6954                                 SymPyValueRangeAnalysis.floordiv(
6955                                     self.var_to_range[i0], ValueRanges.wrap(d)
6956                                 ),
6957                             )
6958                             # Propagate hints (real tensor tracing)
6959                             if i0 in self.unbacked_var_to_val:
6960                                 self.set_unbacked_var_to_val(
6961                                     i1, self.unbacked_var_to_val[i0] // d
6962                                 )
6963                             # Propagate size-like-ness
6964                             if i0 in self.size_like:
6965                                 self.size_like.add(i1)
6966                             self._set_replacement(i0, d * i1, "divisibility")
6967 
6968             except NotImplementedError:
6969                 pass
6970         return
6971 
6972     # See: Note - On 0/1 specialization
6973     def _default_value_range(
6974         self, do_not_specialize_zero_one: bool = False
6975     ) -> ValueRanges:
6976         lower = 0 if (do_not_specialize_zero_one or not self.specialize_zero_one) else 2
6977         return ValueRanges(lower, int_oo)
6978 
6979     def _default_unspecified_value_range(self) -> ValueRanges:
6980         return ValueRanges.unknown_int()
6981 
6982     @_lru_cache
6983     def _simplify_floor_div(self, expr: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
6984         floor_divs = tuple(expr.atoms(FloorDiv))
6985         # we expect floor_divs to be exact,
6986         # and thus add the guards for the exact floordivs,
6987         # even if tracing doesn't require them otherwise
6988         for fd in reversed(floor_divs):
6989             base, divisor = fd.args
6990             mod_expr = Mod(base, divisor)
6991             eq_expr = sympy.Eq(mod_expr, 0)
6992             # add necessary mod guards
6993             self.evaluate_expr(eq_expr)
6994         return self.simplify(expr)
6995 
6996     # We're about to add a guard/runtime assert, check if the ShapeEnv is frozen
6997     # and if so issue a warning
6998     def _check_frozen(self, expr: sympy.Basic, concrete_val: sympy.Basic) -> None:
6999         if self.frozen:
7000             self.counter["ignored_backward_guard"] += 1
7001             signpost_event(
7002                 "dynamic",
7003                 "evaluate_expr_frozen",
7004                 {
7005                     **self.co_fields,
7006                     "ignored_guard": f"{expr} == {concrete_val}",
7007                     # no version = original state (this signpost is expected)
7008                     # version 2 = dynamic backwards is eagerly compiled
7009                     "version": 2,
7010                 },
7011             )
7012             log.info(
7013                 "Ignored guard %s == %s, this could result in accuracy problems",
7014                 expr,
7015                 concrete_val,
7016                 # only print stack trace when debug mode is on (e.g. TORCH_LOGS="dynamic")
7017                 stack_info=True if log.getEffectiveLevel() < logging.WARNING else False,
7018             )
7019 
7020     def _get_user_frame(self) -> Optional[types.FrameType]:
7021         frame = inspect.currentframe()
7022         while frame is not None:
7023             if frame.f_code.co_filename not in uninteresting_files():
7024                 return frame
7025             frame = frame.f_back
7026         return frame
7027 
7028     def _get_stack_summary(
7029         self, is_debug: bool = False, framework_loc: Optional[str] = None
7030     ) -> tuple[SLoc, str]:
7031         floc: Optional[Union[str, traceback.FrameSummary]] = framework_loc
7032         if floc is None:
7033             frame = self._get_user_frame()
7034             try:
7035                 if frame is not None:
7036                     floc = traceback.FrameSummary(
7037                         frame.f_code.co_filename,
7038                         frame.f_lineno,
7039                         frame.f_code.co_name,
7040                     )
7041             finally:
7042                 del frame
7043 
7044         # NB: this stack is truncated, but it's fine because the main
7045         # stack_info will give you the rest of the info you need
7046         maybe_user_loc = None
7047         user_tb = TracingContext.extract_stack()
7048         if user_tb:
7049             idx = len(user_tb) - 1
7050             while idx > 0 and user_tb[idx].filename in uninteresting_files():
7051                 idx -= 1
7052             maybe_user_loc = format_frame(user_tb[idx], line=True)
7053 
7054         maybe_extra_debug = ""
7055         if is_debug and user_tb:
7056             maybe_extra_debug = (
7057                 "\nUser Stack (most recent call last):\n"
7058                 + "  (snipped, see stack below for prefix)\n"
7059                 + "".join(traceback.format_list(user_tb))
7060             )
7061         if is_debug and config.extended_debug_cpp:
7062             cpp_stack = CapturedTraceback.extract(cpp=True)
7063             maybe_extra_debug += "\nC++ stack trace:\n" + "".join(cpp_stack.format())
7064         elif is_debug:
7065             maybe_extra_debug += (
7066                 "\nFor C++ stack trace, run with TORCHDYNAMO_EXTENDED_DEBUG_CPP=1"
7067             )
7068 
7069         return SLoc(floc, maybe_user_loc), maybe_extra_debug
7070 
7071     # Pass in framework_loc to override the framework location info
7072     def _get_sloc(self, framework_loc: Optional[str] = None) -> SLoc:
7073         sloc, _ = self._get_stack_summary(framework_loc=framework_loc)
7074         return sloc
7075 
7076     def _generate_unique_id(self, source_name: str) -> int:
7077         attempt = int(hashlib.sha256(source_name.encode()).hexdigest(), 16) % 100
7078         while attempt in self.unique_ids:
7079             attempt += 1
7080         self.unique_ids.add(attempt)
7081         return attempt
7082 
7083     def _find_frame_locals(self) -> _FrameLocalResult:
7084         """ 
7085         Given the current user code frame, finds the relevant lines of code, 
7086         values of symbolic locals, and free symbols involved. 
7087         """
7088         frame_locals: dict[str, Any] = {}
7089         frame_symbols: dict[str, str] = {}
7090 
7091         if (
7092             frame := _find_user_code_frame()
7093         ) is None or frame.f_code.co_filename == "<string>":
7094             return _FrameLocalResult()
7095 
7096         # find bytecode instructions relevant to the frame
7097         instructions = list(dis.Bytecode(frame.f_code))
7098         co_lines, offset = inspect.getsourcelines(frame.f_code)
7099         start, end, cur = None, None, None
7100         for i, instr in enumerate(instructions):
7101             if instr.starts_line is not None:
7102                 cur = instr.starts_line
7103             if cur != frame.f_lineno:
7104                 continue
7105             if start is None:
7106                 start = end = i
7107             else:
7108                 end = i
7109 
7110         if start is None or end is None:  # no instructions found
7111             return _FrameLocalResult()
7112 
7113         # track involved locals and free symbols
7114         def go(x: Any) -> Optional[str]:
7115             if isinstance(x, torch.Tensor):
7116                 for y in x.size():
7117                     go(y)
7118                 for y in x.stride():
7119                     go(y)
7120                 go(x.storage_offset())
7121                 return (
7122                     f"Tensor(shape: {x.size()}, "
7123                     f"stride: {x.stride()}, "
7124                     f"storage_offset: {x.storage_offset()})"
7125                 )
7126             elif isinstance(x, (SymBool, SymInt, SymFloat)):
7127                 for s in x.node.expr.free_symbols:
7128                     if str(s) in frame_symbols:  # type: ignore[operator]
7129                         continue
7130                     if s in self.var_to_sources:
7131                         frame_symbols[str(s)] = self.var_to_sources[s][0].name()  # type: ignore[assignment]
7132                 return str(x)
7133             return None
7134 
7135         # go through instructions, seeing linenos & involved locals
7136         last_lineno = frame.f_lineno
7137         for instr in instructions[start : end + 1]:
7138             if (lineno := instr.starts_line) is not None:
7139                 last_lineno = max(last_lineno, lineno)
7140             if isinstance(instr.argval, str) and instr.argval in frame.f_locals:
7141                 flat_locals = pytree.tree_flatten(frame.f_locals[instr.argval])[0]
7142                 frame_locals[instr.argval] = [
7143                     go(flat_local) for flat_local in flat_locals
7144                 ]
7145 
7146         # store LOC
7147         locs = co_lines[frame.f_lineno - offset : last_lineno + 1 - offset]
7148         if not locs:
7149             return _FrameLocalResult()
7150 
7151         indent = len(locs[0]) - len(locs[0].lstrip())
7152         frame_loc = "".join([loc[indent:] for loc in locs]).strip()  # type: ignore[assignment]
7153         return _FrameLocalResult(
7154             loc=frame_loc, locals=frame_locals, symbols=frame_symbols
7155         )
7156 
7157     def _log_guard(self, prefix: str, g: SympyBoolean, forcing_spec: bool) -> None:
7158         dtrace_structured(
7159             "guard_added",
7160             metadata_fn=lambda: {
7161                 "expr": str(g),
7162                 "prefix": prefix,
7163                 "expr_node_id": self._expr_sym_node_id,
7164                 "user_stack": structured.get_user_stack(3),
7165                 "stack": structured.get_framework_stack(3),
7166                 "symbol_to_sources": {
7167                     str(v): k
7168                     for k, v in self.source_to_var.items()
7169                     if v in g.free_symbols
7170                 },
7171                 "frame_locals": asdict(self._find_frame_locals()),
7172             },
7173         )
7174         trace_structured(
7175             "guard_added_fast",
7176             metadata_fn=lambda: {
7177                 "expr": str(g),
7178                 "user_stack": structured.from_traceback(TracingContext.extract_stack()),
7179                 "stack": structured.from_traceback(
7180                     CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1).summary()
7181                 ),
7182             },
7183         )
7184         if self.log.isEnabledFor(logging.INFO):
7185             str_g = str(g)
7186             is_debug = (
7187                 config.extended_debug_guard_added is not None
7188                 and str_g == config.extended_debug_guard_added
7189             )
7190             sloc, maybe_extra_debug = self._get_stack_summary(is_debug)
7191             maybe_more_info = ""
7192             if not is_debug:
7193                 maybe_more_info = (
7194                     ", for more info run with "
7195                     f'TORCHDYNAMO_EXTENDED_DEBUG_GUARD_ADDED="{str_g}"'
7196                 )
7197             self.log.info(
7198                 "%s %s [guard added] %s%s%s",
7199                 prefix if not forcing_spec else f"{prefix} (forcing_spec)",
7200                 str_g,
7201                 sloc,
7202                 maybe_more_info,
7203                 maybe_extra_debug,
7204                 stack_info=is_debug,
7205             )
7206 
7207     # A local variable to evaluate_expr stored in the class to avoid
7208     # using it for the lru_cache that is on top of it since it does
7209     # not effect the results. When needed its read directly.
7210     _expr_sym_node_id: Optional[int] = None
7211 
7212     def evaluate_sym_node(
7213         self,
7214         sym_node: SymNode,
7215         size_oblivious: bool = False,
7216         fallback_value: Optional[bool] = None,
7217     ) -> sympy.Basic:
7218         """ 
7219         Given a a SymNode, evaluates sym_node.expr, adding guards if necessary. 
7220         """
7221 
7222         self._expr_sym_node_id = id(sym_node)
7223         return self.evaluate_expr(
7224             sym_node.expr,
7225             sym_node.hint,
7226             sym_node.fx_node,
7227             size_oblivious,
7228             fallback_value=fallback_value,
7229         )
7230 
7231     def _is_python_assert(self) -> bool:
7232         # Check if this boolean is used in an assertion, bytecode pattern for
7233         # assertions is pretty stable for Python 3.7--3.13, ported with minimal
7234         # changes from torch/fx/proxy.py
7235         # Bytecode pattern for `assert` statements:
7236         #     TO_BOOL / COMPARE_OP  # Only for Python >= 3.13
7237         #     POP_JUMP_IF_TRUE
7238         #     LOAD_ASSERTION_ERROR
7239         #     RAISE_VARARGS
7240         frame = self._get_user_frame()
7241         assert frame is not None
7242 
7243         insts = list(dis.get_instructions(frame.f_code))
7244         if sys.version_info >= (3, 11):
7245             # For Python >= 3.11, instructions can be 2-4 bytes long.
7246             from bisect import bisect_left
7247 
7248             cur = bisect_left(insts, frame.f_lasti, key=lambda x: x.offset)
7249         else:
7250             # For Python <= 3.10, instructions are always 2 bytes.
7251             cur = frame.f_lasti // 2
7252 
7253         if sys.version_info >= (3, 13):
7254             if insts[cur].opname in ("TO_BOOL", "COMPARE_OP"):
7255                 # Peek 1 instruction further.
7256                 cur += 1
7257         inst = insts[cur]
7258 
7259         if inst.opname == "POP_JUMP_IF_TRUE" and inst.arg is not None:
7260             first = insts[cur + 1]
7261 
7262             starts_with_assert = (
7263                 first.opname == "LOAD_GLOBAL"
7264                 and first.argval == "AssertionError"
7265                 or first.opname == "LOAD_ASSERTION_ERROR"
7266             )
7267             if starts_with_assert and insts[cur + 2].opname == "RAISE_VARARGS":
7268                 return True
7269         return False
7270 
7271     def _log_real_tensor_propagation(
7272         self, orig_expr: sympy.Basic, unsound_result: sympy.Basic
7273     ) -> None:
7274         log.warning(
7275             "propagate_real_tensors evaluate_expr(%s) -> %s",
7276             orig_expr,
7277             unsound_result,
7278         )
7279         trace_structured(
7280             "propagate_real_tensors",
7281             metadata_fn=lambda: {
7282                 "expr": repr(orig_expr),
7283                 "result": repr(unsound_result),
7284                 "stack": structured.from_traceback(
7285                     CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1).summary()
7286                 ),
7287             },
7288         )
7289         dtrace_structured(
7290             "propagate_real_tensors_provenance",
7291             metadata_fn=lambda: {
7292                 "expr": repr(orig_expr),
7293                 "result": repr(unsound_result),
7294                 "expr_node_id": self._expr_sym_node_id,
7295                 "user_stack": structured.get_user_stack(3),
7296                 "stack": structured.get_framework_stack(3),
7297                 "symbol_to_sources": {
7298                     str(v): k
7299                     for k, v in self.source_to_var.items()
7300                     if v in orig_expr.free_symbols
7301                 },
7302                 "frame_locals": asdict(self._find_frame_locals()),
7303             },
7304         )

7306     def evaluate_expr(
7307         self,
7308         orig_expr: sympy.Basic,
7309         hint: Optional[Union[int, bool, float]] = None,
7310         fx_node: Optional[torch.fx.Node] = None,
7311         size_oblivious: bool = False,
7312         fallback_value: Optional[bool] = None,
7313         *,
7314         forcing_spec: bool = False,
7315     ) -> sympy.Basic:
7316         """ 
7317         Given an expression, evaluates it, adding guards if necessary 
7318         When fallback_value is not None the function return fallback_value instead of failing with data dependent error. 
7319         """
7320 
7321         # Add extra state that evaluate_expr() depends on.
7322         suppress_guards_tls = ShapeEnv._suppress_guards_tls()
7323         return self._inner_evaluate_expr(
7324             orig_expr,
7325             hint,
7326             fx_node,
7327             size_oblivious,
7328             forcing_spec,
7329             suppress_guards_tls,
7330             fallback_value,
7331         )
7332 
7333     @lru_cache(256)
7334     @record_shapeenv_event(save_tracked_fakes=True, name="evaluate_expr")
7335     def _inner_evaluate_expr(
7336         self,
7337         orig_expr: sympy.Basic,
7338         hint: Optional[Union[int, bool, float]],
7339         fx_node: Optional[torch.fx.Node],
7340         size_oblivious: bool,
7341         forcing_spec: bool,
7342         _suppress_guards_tls: bool,
7343         fallback_value: Optional[bool] = None,
7344     ) -> sympy.Basic:
7345         try:
7346             return self._evaluate_expr(
7347                 orig_expr,
7348                 hint,
7349                 fx_node,
7350                 size_oblivious,
7351                 fallback_value,
7352                 forcing_spec=forcing_spec,
7353             )
7354         except Exception as e:
7355             if isinstance(e, GuardOnDataDependentSymNode):
7356                 pass
7357             else:
7358                 self.log.warning(
7359                     "failed during evaluate_expr(%s, hint=%s, size_oblivious=%s, forcing_spec=%s",
7360                     orig_expr,
7361                     hint,
7362                     size_oblivious,
7363                     forcing_spec,
7364                 )
7365             raise
7366 
7367     def _log_suppressed_dde(self, a: SymBool, assumed_value: bool) -> None:
7368         sloc, extra = self._get_stack_summary(True)
7369         log.info(
7370             "could not evaluate %s due to data dependency, it was assumed to be %s with no runtime assertions %s %s",
7371             a,
7372             assumed_value,
7373             sloc,
7374             extra,
7375         )
7376 
7377     def _evaluate_expr(
7378         self,
7379         orig_expr: sympy.Basic,
7380         hint: Optional[Union[bool, int, float]] = None,
7381         fx_node: Optional[torch.fx.Node] = None,
7382         size_oblivious: bool = False,
7383         fallback_value: Optional[bool] = None,
7384         *,
7385         forcing_spec: bool = False,
7386     ) -> sympy.Basic:
7387         # TODO: split conjunctions and evaluate them separately
7388 
7389         if isinstance(
7390             orig_expr,
7391             (sympy.logic.boolalg.BooleanTrue, sympy.logic.boolalg.BooleanFalse),
7392         ):
7393             return orig_expr
7394 
7395         # Don't track this one. (Because this cache is inside this function the
7396         # cache only lasts for the invocation of this function call)
7397         @functools.cache
7398         def compute_concrete_val() -> sympy.Basic:
7399             if hint is None:
7400                 # This is only ever called for expressions WITHOUT unbacked
7401                 # symbols
7402                 r = self.size_hint(orig_expr)
7403                 assert r is not None
7404                 return r
7405             else:
7406                 return sympy.sympify(hint)
7407 
7408         concrete_val: Optional[sympy.Basic]
7409 
7410         # Check if:
7411         #   1. 'translation_validation' is set
7412         #   2. the corresponding 'fx_node' is not 'None'
7413         #   3. the guard should not be suppressed
7414         #   4. the guard doesn't contain backed symfloat symbols
7415         #      since z3 can't handle floats
7416         #   5. fallback_value is none.
7417         # If all of the above check, we create an FX node representing the
7418         # actual expression to be guarded.
7419         node = None
7420         fresh = False
7421         if (
7422             self._translation_validation_enabled
7423             and fx_node is not None
7424             and not self._suppress_guards_tls()
7425             and not size_oblivious
7426             and not any(symbol_is_type(s, SymT.FLOAT) for s in orig_expr.free_symbols)
7427             and fallback_value is None
7428         ):
7429             # TODO: does this even worked with unbacked :think:
7430             concrete_val = compute_concrete_val()
7431             if concrete_val is sympy.true:
7432                 node, fresh = self._create_fx_call_function(torch._assert, (fx_node,))
7433             elif concrete_val is sympy.false:
7434                 neg, _ = self._create_fx_call_function(operator.not_, (fx_node,))
7435                 node, fresh = self._create_fx_call_function(torch._assert, (neg,))
7436             else:
7437                 eql, _ = self._create_fx_call_function(
7438                     operator.eq, (fx_node, concrete_val)
7439                 )
7440                 node, fresh = self._create_fx_call_function(torch._assert, (eql,))
7441 
7442             assert node is not None
7443             # If this is a fresh node, we have to remember the event index that
7444             # corresponds to this assertion node.
7445             # Reason: so that, given an assertion node, we can replay the ShapeEnv
7446             # events until the point where this assertion node was freshly created.
7447             if fresh:
7448                 self._add_fx_node_metadata(node)
7449 
7450         # After creating the FX node corresponding to orig_expr, we must make sure that
7451         # no error will be raised until the end of this function.
7452         #
7453         # Reason: the translation validation may become invalid otherwise.
7454         #
7455         # If an error is raised before the end of this function, we remove the FX node
7456         # inserted, and re-raise the error.
7457         guard = None
7458 
7459         try:
7460             if orig_expr.is_number:
7461                 self.log.debug("eval %s [trivial]", orig_expr)
7462                 if hint is not None:
7463                     if isinstance(hint, bool):
7464                         assert orig_expr == hint, f"{orig_expr} != {hint}"
7465                     else:
7466                         assert sympy.Eq(orig_expr, hint), f"{orig_expr} != {hint}"
7467                 return orig_expr
7468 
7469             expr = orig_expr
7470 
7471             static_expr = self._maybe_evaluate_static(
7472                 expr, size_oblivious=size_oblivious
7473             )
7474             if static_expr is not None:
7475                 self.log.debug(
7476                     "eval %s == %s [statically known]",
7477                     (
7478                         f"size_oblivious({orig_expr})"
7479                         if size_oblivious
7480                         else size_oblivious
7481                     ),
7482                     static_expr,
7483                 )
7484                 if (
7485                     not size_oblivious
7486                     and config.backed_size_oblivious
7487                     and hint is not None
7488                 ):
7489                     # TODO: maybe reconcile this with use of counterfactual hints
7490                     # in unbacked case
7491                     assert static_expr == hint, f"{static_expr} != {hint}"
7492                 return static_expr
7493 
7494             transmute_into_runtime_assert = False
7495 
7496             concrete_val = None
7497             if not (expr.free_symbols <= self.var_to_val.keys()):
7498                 # TODO: dedupe this with _maybe_evaluate_static
7499                 # Attempt to eliminate the unbacked SymInt
7500                 new_expr = self._maybe_evaluate_static(expr, unbacked_only=True)
7501                 assert new_expr is not None
7502                 if not (new_expr.free_symbols <= self.var_to_val.keys()):
7503                     ok = False
7504 
7505                     # fallback_value is set when guard_or_true or guard_or_false are used.
7506                     if not ok and fallback_value is not None:
7507                         self._log_suppressed_dde(orig_expr, fallback_value)
7508                         return fallback_value
7509 
7510                     # oblivious_var_to_val will be defined iff we have sizes with DimDynamic.OBLIVIOUS_SIZE type.
7511                     # See https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/137100#issuecomment-2495778113
7512                     if (
7513                         self.oblivious_var_to_val
7514                         and not (
7515                             correct_hint := orig_expr.xreplace(
7516                                 self.oblivious_var_to_val
7517                             )
7518                         ).free_symbols
7519                         and not (
7520                             counterfactual_hint := orig_expr.xreplace(
7521                                 {
7522                                     k: max(2, v)
7523                                     for k, v in self.oblivious_var_to_val.items()
7524                                 }
7525                             )
7526                         ).free_symbols
7527                         and correct_hint == counterfactual_hint
7528                     ):
7529                         # TODO: better logging
7530                         log.info(
7531                             "oblivious_size %s -> %s (passed counterfactual)",
7532                             orig_expr,
7533                             correct_hint,
7534                         )
7535                         concrete_val = correct_hint
7536                         # NB: do NOT transmute into runtime assert
7537                         ok = True
7538 
7539                     # unbacked_var_to_val is not None iff propagate_real_tensors is on.
7540                     # if propagate_real_tensors is on, we check the example values to generate (unsound_result)
7541                     # and if they pass we add a runtime assertions and continue.
7542                     if (
7543                         not ok
7544                         and self.unbacked_var_to_val
7545                         and not (
7546                             unsound_result := orig_expr.xreplace(
7547                                 self.unbacked_var_to_val
7548                             ).xreplace(self.var_to_val)
7549                         ).free_symbols
7550                     ):
7551                         self._log_real_tensor_propagation(orig_expr, unsound_result)
7552                         transmute_into_runtime_assert = True
7553                         concrete_val = unsound_result
7554                         ok = True
7555 
7556                     # Check if this is coming from a python assert statement, if so, convert it to a runtime assertion
7557                     # instead of failing.
7558                     if not ok and self.trace_asserts and self._is_python_assert():
7559                         concrete_val = sympy.true
7560                         transmute_into_runtime_assert = True
7561                         ok = True
7562 
7563                     if not ok:
7564                         size_oblivious_result = None
7565                         # compute size_oblivious_result to suggest it as a fix for the user if it works.
7566                         if not size_oblivious:
7567                             size_oblivious_result = self._maybe_evaluate_static(
7568                                 expr, size_oblivious=True
7569                             )
7570                         raise self._make_data_dependent_error(
7571                             expr.xreplace(self.var_to_val),
7572                             expr,
7573                             size_oblivious_result=size_oblivious_result,
7574                             expr_sym_node_id=self._expr_sym_node_id,
7575                         )
7576                 else:
7577                     expr = new_expr
7578 
7579             if concrete_val is None:
7580                 concrete_val = compute_concrete_val()
7581             self._check_frozen(expr, concrete_val)
7582 
7583             if (
7584                 config.inject_EVALUATE_EXPR_flip_equality_TESTING_ONLY
7585                 and isinstance(hint, bool)
7586                 and isinstance(expr, (sympy.Eq, sympy.Ne))
7587             ):
7588                 expr = sympy.Not(expr)
7589 
7590             # Turn this into a boolean expression, no longer need to consult
7591             # concrete_val
7592             if concrete_val is sympy.true:
7593                 g = cast(SympyBoolean, expr)
7594             elif concrete_val is sympy.false:
7595                 g = sympy.Not(expr)
7596             else:
7597                 g = sympy.Eq(expr, concrete_val)  # type: ignore[arg-type]
7598 
7599             if transmute_into_runtime_assert:
7600                 self.guard_or_defer_runtime_assert(
7601                     g, f"propagate_real_tensors: {orig_expr} == {concrete_val}"
7602                 )
7603                 return concrete_val
7604 
7605             if not self._suppress_guards_tls():
7606                 self._log_guard("eval", g, forcing_spec=forcing_spec)
7607 
7608                 # TODO: If we successfully eliminate a symbol via equality, it
7609                 # is not actually necessary to save a guard for the equality,
7610                 # as we will implicitly generate a guard when we match that
7611                 # input against the symbol.  Probably the easiest way to
7612                 # implement this is to have maybe_guard_rel return a bool
7613                 # saying if it "subsumed" the guard (and therefore the guard
7614                 # is no longer necessary)
7615                 self._maybe_guard_rel(g)
7616 
7617                 if not self.allow_complex_guards_as_runtime_asserts:
7618                     # at this point, we've evaluated the concrete expr value, and have
7619                     # flipped/negated the guard if necessary. Now we know what to guard
7620                     # or defer to runtime assert on.
7621                     guard = ShapeGuard(
7622                         g, self._get_sloc(), size_oblivious=size_oblivious
7623                     )
7624                     self.guards.append(guard)
7625                     self.axioms.update(dict(self.get_implications(self.simplify(g))))
7626                 else:
7627                     # it's fine to defer simple guards here without checking,
7628                     # the _maybe_guard_rel() call above will set replacements if possible,
7629                     # and so the result here will be statically known
7630                     self.guard_or_defer_runtime_assert(g, f"evaluate_expr: {orig_expr}")
7631             else:
7632                 self._log_guard("eval [guard suppressed]", g, forcing_spec=forcing_spec)
7633 
7634         except Exception:
7635             if fresh:
7636                 self._remove_fx_node(node)
7637             raise
7638 
7639         if not self._suppress_guards_tls():
7640             if guard is not None:  # we might have deferred this to runtime assert
7641                 for s in g.free_symbols:
7642                     self.symbol_guard_counter[s] += 1
7643                     # Forcing_spec to avoid infinite recursion
7644                     if (
7645                         not forcing_spec
7646                         and config.symbol_guard_limit_before_specialize is not None
7647                         and self.symbol_guard_counter[s]
7648                         > config.symbol_guard_limit_before_specialize
7649                     ):
7650                         # Force specialization
7651                         self.log.info(
7652                             "symbol_guard_limit_before_specialize=%s exceeded on %s",
7653                             config.symbol_guard_limit_before_specialize,
7654                             s,
7655                         )
7656                         self.evaluate_expr(s, forcing_spec=True)
7657 
7658         return concrete_val
7659 
7660     def cleanup(self) -> None:
7661         """ 
7662         Break reference cycles. 
7663  
7664         This destroys the stacks. If you really want to keep them, we 
7665         just need some way to break references on code objects. 
7666         """
7667         for s in self.var_to_stack.values():
7668             s.cleanup()
7669         for ras in self.deferred_runtime_asserts.values():
7670             for ra in ras:
7671                 ra.stack.cleanup()
7672 
7673     @lru_cache(256)
7674     @record_shapeenv_event(save_tracked_fakes=True)
7675     def guard_or_defer_runtime_assert(
7676         self, orig_expr: SympyBoolean, msg: str, fx_node: Optional[torch.fx.Node] = None
7677     ) -> bool:
7678         """ 
7679         Adds a guard that orig_expr is True if we can or fall back to adding an assert 
7680         that is checked at runtime. 
7681  
7682         Args: 
7683             orig_expr (sympy.Expr): Boolean expression to assert is true 
7684             msg (str): Message to display on assertion failure 
7685             fx_node (Optional, torch.fx.Node): node in ``self.graph`` corresponding 
7686                 to the expression, if applicable 
7687         """
7688         expr = orig_expr
7689 
7690         # TODO: split conjunctions and evaluate them separately
7691 
7692         static_expr = self._maybe_evaluate_static(expr)
7693         if static_expr is not None:
7694             self.log.debug(
7695                 "runtime_assert %s == %s [statically known]", orig_expr, static_expr
7696             )
7697             # TODO: assert bool(static_expr)
7698             return bool(static_expr)
7699 
7700         # Attempt to eliminate the unbacked SymInt
7701         new_expr = self._maybe_evaluate_static(expr, unbacked_only=True)
7702         assert new_expr is not None
7703         if (
7704             not self.prefer_deferred_runtime_asserts_over_guards
7705             and new_expr.free_symbols <= self.var_to_val.keys()
7706         ):
7707             # Do a normal guard
7708             return self.evaluate_expr(new_expr, fx_node=fx_node)
7709         # NB: Don't use new_expr as expr; it could contain gunk like shape0
7710         # which we don't want to guard on
7711 
7712         if (
7713             self._translation_validation_enabled
7714             and fx_node is not None
7715             and not self._suppress_guards_tls()
7716         ):
7717             node, fresh = self._create_fx_call_function(torch._assert, (fx_node,))
7718             assert node is not None
7719             if fresh:
7720                 self._add_fx_node_metadata(node)
7721 
7722         if not self._suppress_guards_tls():
7723             self._log_guard("runtime_assert", orig_expr, forcing_spec=False)
7724             # If you're here because of this assert, read Note [Backwards runtime asserts]
7725             # in torch/_inductor/graph.py
7726             if self.runtime_asserts_frozen:
7727                 log.debug("runtime_asserts_frozen but then got %s", expr)
7728             self._check_frozen(expr, sympy.true)
7729             # eliminate symbols on equality tests / refine ranges
7730             self._maybe_guard_rel(expr)
7731 
7732             # canonicalise to remove equations that are trivially equal
7733             orig_expr = expr
7734             expr = canonicalize_bool_expr(expr)
7735             stack = CapturedTraceback.extract(skip=1)
7736             ra = RuntimeAssert(expr, msg, stack)
7737             # TODO: Do this in a way that is less janky than int(s.name[1:])
7738             cands = sorted(
7739                 (s for s in expr.free_symbols if symbol_is_type(s, SymT.UNBACKED_INT)),
7740                 key=lambda s: int(s.name[1:]),
7741             )
7742             # Is None when prefer_deferred_runtime_asserts_over_guards=True
7743             # and the guard in question has no unbacked SymInts in front
7744             ix = cands[-1] if cands else None
7745             self.deferred_runtime_asserts.setdefault(ix, []).append(ra)
7746             self.axioms.update(dict(self.get_implications(self.simplify(expr))))
7747             self.num_deferred_runtime_asserts += 1
7748             self._update_version_counter()
7749         else:
7750             self._log_guard(
7751                 "runtime_assert [guard suppressed]", orig_expr, forcing_spec=False
7752             )
7753 
7754         return True
7755 
7756     # Refines the ranges of the variables present in 'guard'.
7757     #
7758     # This function tries to refine the range of the variables inside
7759     # 'guard' by reasoning about it. Specifically, when 'guard' is a
7760     # 'sympy.Relational' operation.
7761     #
7762     # It does mainly 3 things:
7763     #   1. Tries to isolate a variable in the left-hand side
7764     #   2. Compute the value range of the right-hand side
7765     #   3. Update the value range of the variable, if better
7766     def _refine_ranges(self, expr: SympyBoolean) -> None:
7767         expr = self.simplify(expr)
7768 
7769         for symbol in expr.free_symbols:
7770             assert isinstance(symbol, sympy.Symbol)
7771 
7772             if isinstance(self.var_to_val.get(symbol, None), SingletonInt):
7773                 # Skip var_to_range logic for SingletonInt which is only used
7774                 # for jagged layout NestedTensors today
7775                 continue
7776 
7777             r = try_solve(expr, symbol)
7778 
7779             if r is None or not (symbol.is_integer and r[1].is_integer):
7780                 # Range refinement only supports integer symbols for now.
7781                 # There are lots of SymPy bugs when it comes to comparing
7782                 # reals and integers, so we skip that for now.
7783                 continue
7784 
7785             r_expr, rhs = r
7786             vr = self.var_to_range[symbol]
7787             lower, upper = vr.lower, vr.upper
7788 
7789             rhs_vr = bound_sympy(rhs, self.var_to_range)
7790 
7791             # Let's suppose that we have a preexisting range for x [0, 100].
7792             # Now, we issue a guard x > y, where the range for y is [50, 150].
7793             # Then, lower = 0, rhs_vr.lower = 50 and therefore refinement can happen,
7794             # refining x to [51, 100], since x must be greater than y, but the lowest
7795             # y could be is 50.
7796             #
7797             # sympy.Eq may update both lower and upper bounds.
7798             # sympy.G{t,e} may update the lower bound, only.
7799             # sympy.L{t,e} may update the upper bound, only.
7800             if lower < rhs_vr.lower and isinstance(
7801                 r_expr, (sympy.Eq, sympy.Ge, sympy.Gt)
7802             ):
7803                 # Strictly greater relations allow us to refine a bit more, since
7804                 # x < y implies that the lower bound for x is: y + 1.
7805                 lower = rhs_vr.lower + int(isinstance(r_expr, sympy.Gt))
7806             if upper > rhs_vr.upper and isinstance(
7807                 r_expr, (sympy.Eq, sympy.Le, sympy.Lt)
7808             ):
7809                 upper = rhs_vr.upper - int(isinstance(r_expr, sympy.Lt))
7810 
7811             # Do nothing if the new value range is no better than what we already have.
7812             if vr == ValueRanges(lower, upper):
7813                 continue
7814 
7815             # Updates the range and the guards corresponding to each bound of the symbol.
7816             self._update_var_to_range(symbol, ValueRanges(lower, upper))
7817             # If the range is refined to singleton, set replacement
7818             if self.var_to_range[symbol].is_singleton():
7819                 self._set_replacement(
7820                     symbol,
7821                     self.var_to_range[symbol].lower,
7822                     "range_refined_to_singleton",
7823                 )
7824 
7825             # Clears the cache, since this update can change the result.
7826             self._maybe_evaluate_static.cache_clear()
7827 
7828     @lru_cache(maxsize=None)
7829     @record_shapeenv_event()
7830     def constrain_symbol_range(
7831         self, s: sympy.Symbol, compiler_min: int, compiler_max: int
7832     ) -> None:
7833         upd_vr = ValueRanges(compiler_min, compiler_max)
7834         old_vr = self.var_to_range.get(s, ValueRanges.unknown())
7835         self._update_var_to_range(s, upd_vr)
7836         if (new_vr := self.var_to_range[s]) != old_vr:
7837             log.info(
7838                 "constrain_symbol_range %s [%s, %s]", s, new_vr.lower, new_vr.upper
7839             )
7840 
7841 
7842 def _is_int(expr: object) -> bool:
7843     return isinstance(expr, SymInt) and expr.node.expr.is_number
7844

7846 # WARNING: This is legacy, DO NOT USE
7847 def _is_dim_dynamic(t: torch.Tensor, d: int) -> bool:
7848     return hasattr(t, "_dynamo_dynamic_indices") and d in t._dynamo_dynamic_indices

7851 class PropagateUnbackedSymInts(torch.fx.Interpreter):
7852     def run_node(self, n: torch.fx.Node) -> Result:
7853         """ 
7854         Run an FX node, propagating unbacked Symbol bindings to the new fake tensor 
7855         """
7856         from torch._guards import detect_fake_mode
7857 
7858         result = super().run_node(n)
7859         rebind_unbacked(detect_fake_mode().shape_env, n, result)
7860         return result

7862 
7863 def _find_user_code_frame() -> Optional[types.FrameType]:
7864     frame = inspect.currentframe()
7865     while frame is not None:
7866         if not frame.f_code.co_filename.startswith(
7867             os.path.dirname(inspect.getfile(torch)) + os.path.sep
7868         ):
7869             break
7870         frame = frame.f_back
7871     return frame
7872 
7873 
7874 def _blame_user_code(e: Exception, frame: types.FrameType) -> None:
7875     frame_summary = traceback.FrameSummary(
7876         frame.f_code.co_filename,
7877         frame.f_lineno,
7878         frame.f_code.co_name,
7879     )
7880     msg = e.args[0]
7881     msg += "\n\nThe following call raised this error:\n" + "".join(
7882         traceback.StackSummary.from_list([frame_summary]).format()
7883     )
7884     e.args = (msg,)
7885 
7886 
7887 class _PythonMsgPrinter(PythonPrinter):
7888     """ 
7889     Util printer that replaces sympy symbols with their source-level names 
7890     and renders sympy relational operators (e.g., Eq, Ne, Ge, Le) inline 
7891     (i.e., as ==, !=, >, <). 
7892     """
7893 
7894     def __init__(self, src_map: dict[str, list[str]]) -> None:
7895         super().__init__()
7896         self.src_map = src_map
7897 
7898     def _print_Symbol(self, sym: sympy.Symbol) -> str:
7899         return self.src_map[sym.name][0]
7900 
7901 
7902 def _is_non_negative_check(cond: sympy.Basic) -> Optional[str]:
7903     """ 
7904     Check if a condition (SymPy expression) is checking for non-negative values (>= 0). 
7905     Returns the variable name if it's a non-negative check (>= 0), None otherwise. 
7906     """
7907     if isinstance(cond, sympy.Rel):
7908         if cond.rel_op == ">=" and cond.rhs == 0:
7909             return str(cond.lhs)
7910     return None
7911 
7912 
7913 def _suggest_torch_checks(
7914     e: GuardOnDataDependentSymNode, src_map: defaultdict[str, list[str]]
7915 ) -> None:
7916     """ 
7917     Enhances a GuardOnDataDependentSymNode error with suggested fixes using torch._check. 
7918  
7919     This function analyzes the condition that caused the data-dependent error and generates 
7920     user-friendly suggestions for fixing it by adding appropriate torch._check calls. 
7921     It handles special cases like non-negative checks with specific recommendations. 
7922  
7923     Args: 
7924         e: The GuardOnDataDependentSymNode error to enhance with suggestions 
7925         src_map: A mapping from symbol names to their corresponding source-level variable names 
7926  
7927     Returns: 
7928         None. Modifies the error message in-place by updating e.args[0]. 
7929     """
7930     # extract the unresolved condition on unbacked symints in the error
7931     cond = e.cond
7932     diff = ", ".join(s.name for s in cond.free_symbols if s.name not in src_map)
7933     if diff:
7934         log.warning("Unable to find user code corresponding to {%s}", diff)
7935         return
7936     printer = _PythonMsgPrinter(src_map)
7937     msg = e.args[0]
7938     msg += "\nTo fix the error, insert one of the following checks before this call:"
7939 
7940     not_cond_str = printer.doprint(sympy.Not(cond))
7941     var_name = _is_non_negative_check(cond)
7942 
7943     # suggested fixes to resolve `cond` are to tell the compiler to assume
7944     # either `cond` or its negation (the user will need to select which)
7945     suggested_fixes = []
7946 
7947     if var_name:
7948         suggested_fixes = [
7949             f"You can add either: torch._check_is_size({var_name}) or torch._check({var_name}>=0)"
7950             f" Note: torch._check_is_size({var_name}) could prevent data dependent errors that"
7951             + " happen in a guard_size_oblivious(..) context by opting into guard_size_oblivious reasoning."
7952             + " See documentation on guard_size_oblivious for more details:"
7953             + " https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/generated/torch.fx.experimental.symbolic_shapes.guard_size_oblivious.html",
7954             f"torch._check({not_cond_str})",
7955         ]
7956     else:
7957         suggested_fixes = [
7958             f"torch._check({printer.doprint(cond)})",
7959             f"torch._check({not_cond_str})",
7960         ]
7961 
7962     for i, fix in enumerate(suggested_fixes):
7963         msg += f"\n  {i + 1}. {fix}"
7964     src_mapped = ", ".join(
7965         f"`{s}` with {' or '.join(src_map[s])}"
7966         for s in sorted(s.name for s in cond.free_symbols)
7967     )
7968     msg += f"\n\n(These suggested fixes were derived by replacing {src_mapped} in {cond} and its negation.)"
7969     e.args = (msg,)
7970 
7971 
7972 def _suggest_fixes_for_data_dependent_error_non_strict(
7973     e: GuardOnDataDependentSymNode,
7974 ) -> None:
7975     """ 
7976     Given a raised data-dependent error, add the following to the error message: 
7977     1. the closest user code location that raised the error; 
7978     2. suggested fixes for the error in terms of live variables at that location. 
7979     """
7980 
7981     # walk the stack up from the data-dependent error until a non-torch frame is found
7982     frame = _find_user_code_frame()
7983     if frame is not None:
7984         # add frame info to error message
7985         _blame_user_code(e, frame)
7986 
7987         # map symbol names reachable via frame locals to their source-level names
7988         src_map = defaultdict(list)
7989         for var, val in frame.f_locals.items():
7990             try:
7991                 tree_leaves_with_path = pytree.tree_leaves_with_path(val)
7992             except ValueError:
7993                 log.warning(
7994                     "pytree.tree_leaves_with_path failed for value of type {%s} in local variable {%s}",
7995                     type(val),
7996                     var,
7997                 )
7998                 continue
7999             # figure out how to access any symbol inside `val` through `var`
8000             for path, leaf in tree_leaves_with_path:
8001                 name = var + pytree.keystr(path)
8002                 if isinstance(leaf, torch.SymInt):
8003                     src_map[str(leaf.node.expr)].append(name)
8004                 elif isinstance(leaf, torch.Tensor):
8005                     for i, dim in enumerate(leaf.shape):
8006                         if isinstance(dim, torch.SymInt):
8007                             src_map[str(dim.node.expr)].append(f"{name}.shape[{i}]")
8008 
8009         # add suggested torch.check()s based on `src_map` to the error message
8010         # replacing unbacked symints in the unresolved condition in the error
8011         if isinstance(e.cond, sympy.logic.boolalg.Boolean):
8012             _suggest_torch_checks(e, src_map)
8013 
8014 
8015 @contextmanager
8016 def _remove_effect_token_unbacked_bindings(
8017     node: torch.fx.Node,
8018 ) -> Generator[None, None, None]:
8019     """ 
8020     Temporarily modifies unbacked_bindings in a node's metadata by removing the first element 
8021     of each path, which corresponds to an effect token. 
8022  
8023     This is used when processing nodes that have effect tokens as the first element in their 
8024     unbacked_bindings paths. The context manager ensures that the original bindings are 
8025     restored after the operation is complete. 
8026  
8027     Args: 
8028         node: The FX node whose unbacked_bindings will be temporarily modified 
8029  
8030     Yields: 
8031         None 
8032     """
8033     old_bindings = node.meta.get("unbacked_bindings", {})
8034 
8035     # Remove the extra layer for effect token
8036     new_bindings = {k: path[1:] if path else path for k, path in old_bindings.items()}
8037 
8038     node.meta["unbacked_bindings"] = new_bindings
8039 
8040     try:
8041         yield
8042     finally:
8043         node.meta["unbacked_bindings"] = old_bindings
8044 
8045 
8046 # This helper function is used in passes that insert runtime assertions in the graph.
8047 # When accessing expressions representing input placeholders, we do not apply replacements
8048 # since those inputs should be seen by assertions that use them to be inserted. The only replacement
8049 # that we apply is unbacked renaming.
8050 def _get_placeholder_expr(sym_node: SymNode) -> sympy.Expr:
8051     shape_env = sym_node.shape_env
8052     result = sym_node._expr
8053     if result in shape_env.unbacked_renamings:
8054         return shape_env.unbacked_renamings[result]
8055     return result
8056
